  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s History after the Exodus"
      title: "Israel\u2019s History after the Exodus"
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the words which Moses spoke to all Israel [while they
        were still] beyond [that is, on the east side of] the Jordan [River] in the
        wilderness [across from Jerusalem], in the Arabah [the long, deep valley
        running north and south from the eastern arm of the Red Sea to beyond the
        Dead Sea] opposite Suph, between Paran and Tophel and Laban and Hazeroth
        and Dizahab (place of gold). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It is [only] eleven days\u2019 journey from Horeb (Mount Sinai) by
        way of Mount Seir to Kadesh-barnea [on Canaan\u2019s border; yet Israel wandered
        in the wilderness for forty years before crossing the border and entering
        Canaan, the promised land]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the fortieth year, on the first day of the eleventh month, Moses
        spoke to the children of Israel in accordance with all that the Lord had
        commanded him to say to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'after he had defeated Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived in
        Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan, who lived at Ashtaroth in Edrei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Beyond (east of) the Jordan in the land of Moab, Moses began to explain
        this law, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe Lord our God spoke to us at Horeb, saying, \u2018You have
        stayed long enough on this mountain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Turn and resume your journey, and go to the hill country of the Amorites,
        and to all their neighbors in the Arabah, in the hill country and in the
        lowland (the Shephelah), in the Negev (South country) and on the coast of
        the [Mediterranean] Sea, the land of the Canaanites, and Lebanon, as far
        as the great river, the river Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Look, I have set the land before you; go in and take possession of
        the land which the Lord swore (solemnly promised) to your fathers, to Abraham,
        to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give to them and to their descendants after them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI spoke to you at that time, saying, \u2018I am not able to
        bear the burden of you alone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord your God has multiplied you, and look, today you are as
        numerous as the stars of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'May the Lord, the God of your fathers, add to you a thousand times
        as many as you are and bless you, just as He has promised you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'How can I alone bear the weight and pressure and burden of you and
        your strife (contention) and complaining? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Choose for yourselves wise, understanding, experienced, and respected
        men from your tribes, and I will appoint them as heads (leaders) over you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And you answered me, \u2018The thing which you have said to do is
        good.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I took the leaders of your tribes, wise and experienced men, and
        made them leaders over you, commanders of thousands, and hundreds, and fifties,
        and tens, and officers (administrators) for your tribes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThen I commanded your judges at that time, saying, \u2018Hear
        the matters between your brothers [your fellow countrymen], and judge righteously
        and fairly between a man and his brother, or the stranger (resident alien,
        foreigner) who is with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You shall not show partiality in judgment; you shall hear and pay
        attention to the [cases of the] least [important] as well as the great. You
        shall not fear man, for the judgment is God\u2019s. The case that is too
        hard for you [to judge], you shall bring to me, and I will hear it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I commanded you at that time [regarding] all the things that you
        should do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen we set out from Horeb (Sinai), and went through all that
        great and terrible wilderness which you saw on the way to the hill country
        of the Amorites, just as the Lord our God commanded us; and we came to Kadesh-barnea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And I said to you, \u2018You have come to the hill country of the
        Amorites which the Lord our God is about to give us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Behold, the Lord your God has set the land before you; go up and
        take possession of it, just as the Lord, the God of your fathers, has spoken
        to you. Do not fear or be dismayed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThen all of you approached me and said, \u2018Let us send men
        [into the land] before us, so that they may explore and search the area for
        us, and bring back to us word regarding the way we should go, and the cities
        we should enter.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The plan pleased me and I took twelve of your men, one man from each
        tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They turned and went up into the hill country, and came to the Valley
        of Eshcol and spied it out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then they took some of the fruit of the land in their hands and brought
        it down to us; and they reported back to us, and said, \u2018It is a good
        land which the Lord our God is about to give us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYet you were not willing to go up [to take possession of it],
        but rebelled against the command of the Lord your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "You murmured and were ill-tempered (discontented) in your tents,
        and said, \u2018Because the Lord hates us He has brought us from the land
        of Egypt to hand us over to the Amorites to destroy us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Where can we go up? Our brothers (spies) have made our hearts melt
        [in fear] and demoralized us by saying, \u201CThe people are bigger and taller
        than we; the cities are large, and fortified [all the way up] to heaven.
        And besides, we saw the [giant-like] sons of the Anakim there.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then I said to you, \u2018Do not be shocked, nor fear them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The Lord your God who goes before you will fight for you Himself,
        just as He did for you in Egypt before your [very] eyes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and in the wilderness where you saw how the Lord your God carried
        and protected you, just as a man carries his son, all along the way which
        you traveled until you arrived at this place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Yet in spite of this word, you did not trust [that is, confidently
        rely on and believe] the Lord your God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'who went before you along the way, in fire by night and in a cloud
        by day, to seek a place for you to make camp and to show you the way in which
        you should go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CAnd the Lord heard the sound of your words, and He was angry
        and took an oath, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Not one of these men, this evil generation, shall see the good
        land which I swore (solemnly promised) to give to your fathers, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "except Caleb the son of Jephunneh; he shall see it, and to him and
        to his children I will give the land on which he has walked, because he has
        followed the Lord completely [and remained true to Him].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "The Lord was angry with me also because of you, saying, \u2018Not
        even you shall enter Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joshua the son of Nun, who stands before you, he shall enter there.
        Encourage and strengthen him, for he shall cause Israel to inherit it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Moreover, your little ones whom you said would become prey, and your
        sons, who today have no knowledge of good or evil, shall enter Canaan, and
        I will give it to them and they shall possess it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But as for you, turn around and set out for the wilderness by way
        of the Red Sea (Sea of Reeds).\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CThen you answered and said to me, \u2018We have sinned against
        the Lord. We will go up and fight, just as the Lord our God has commanded
        us.\u2019 So you equipped every man with weapons of war, and regarded it
        as easy to go up into the hill country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But the Lord said to me, \u2018Say to them, \u201CDo not go up and
        do not fight, for I am not among you [because of your rebellion]; otherwise
        you will be [badly] defeated by your enemies.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So I spoke to you, but you would not listen. Instead you rebelled
        against the command of the Lord, and acted presumptuously and went up into
        the hill country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Then the Amorites who lived in that hill country came out against
        you and chased you as bees do, and struck you down in Seir as far as Hormah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And you returned and wept before the Lord; but the Lord would not
        listen to your voice nor pay attention to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: So you stayed in Kadesh; many days you stayed there.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wanderings in the Wilderness'
      title: Wanderings in the Wilderness
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThen we turned and set out for the wilderness by the way
        of the Red Sea, just as the Lord had told me; and we circled Mount Seir for
        many days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Lord spoke to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018You have circled this mountain long enough; turn northward, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and command the people, saying, \u201CYou are passing through the
        territory of your brothers the sons of Esau (the Edomites), who live in Seir;
        and they will be afraid of you. So be very careful; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'do not provoke them, for I will not give you any of their land, not
        even as little as a footstep, because I have given Mount Seir to Esau as
        a possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall buy food from them with money so that you may [have something
        to] eat, and you shall also buy water from them with money so that you may
        [have something to] drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For the Lord your God has blessed you in all that you have done;
        He has known about your wanderings through this great wilderness. These forty
        years the Lord your God has been with you; you have lacked nothing.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSo we passed beyond our brothers the sons of Esau, who lived
        in Seir, away from the Arabah (wilderness) road, away from Elath and from
        Ezion-geber. Then we turned and passed through by the way of the Wilderness
        of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u2018Do not harass [the descendants of]
        Moab, nor provoke them to war, for I will not give you any of their land
        as a possession, because I have given Ar to the sons (Moab and Ammon) of
        Lot as a possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '(The Emim lived there in times past, a people great and numerous,
        and as tall as the Anakim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'These also are regarded as Rephaim [an ancient people], as are the
        Anakim, but the Moabites call them Emim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Horites also used to live in Seir, but the sons of Esau dispossessed
        them. They destroyed them from before them and settled in their place, just
        as Israel did in the land which the Lord gave them as their possession.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018Now arise and cross the valley of the Zered.\u2019 So we crossed
        the Zered Valley. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now thirty-eight years passed from the time we left Kadesh-barnea
        until we crossed the Zered Valley, until that entire generation of the men
        of war had died from within the camp, just as the Lord had sworn to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover the hand of the Lord was against them, to destroy them from
        within the camp, until they were all dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CSo it came about when all the men of war had finally died from
        among the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'that the Lord spoke to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Today you are to pass through Ar, the border of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When you come opposite the territory of the sons of Ammon, do not
        harass them nor provoke them, for I will not give you any of the land of
        the sons of Ammon as a possession, because I have given it to the sons of
        Lot as a possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '(It is also regarded as the land of the Rephaim [of giant stature],
        for Rephaim used to live there, but the Ammonites call them Zamzummin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'a great, numerous people, and tall as the Anakim, but the Lord destroyed
        them before the sons of Ammon. And they dispossessed them and settled in
        their place, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'just as He did for the sons of Esau, who live in Seir, when He destroyed
        the Horites from before them; and the sons of Esau (the Edomites) dispossessed
        them and settled in their place [and remain there] even to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As for the Avvim, who lived in villages as far as Gaza, the Caphtorim
        (Cretans, later Philistines) who came from Caphtor (Crete) destroyed them
        and settled in their place.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Now arise, continue on, and go through the valley of the Arnon.
        Look, I have handed over to you Sihon the Amorite, king of Heshbon, and his
        land. Begin! Take possession [of it] and fight with him in battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This day I will begin to put the dread and the fear of you on the
        peoples (pagans) under the whole heaven, who, when they hear the reports
        about you, will tremble and be in anguish because of you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CSo I sent messengers from the Wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon
        king of Heshbon with words of peace, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018Let me pass through your land [with my people]. I will travel
        [with them] only on the highway; I will not turn away to the right or to
        the left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You will sell me food for money so that I [along with my people]
        will eat, and you will give me water for money so that I [along with my people]
        will drink; only let me [and my people] travel through [the land] on foot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "just as the sons of Esau, who live in Seir, and the Moabites, who
        live in Ar, did for me, until I cross the Jordan into the land which the
        Lord our God is giving us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But Sihon king of Heshbon was not willing for us to travel through
        his land; for the Lord your God hardened his spirit and made his heart obstinate,
        in order to hand him over to you, as he is today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The Lord said to me, \u2018Look, I have begun to hand over to you
        Sihon and his land. Begin! Take possession [of it], so that you may possess
        his land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CThen at Jahaz, Sihon and all his people came out to meet us
        in battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So the Lord our God handed him over to us [and gave us the victory],
        and we defeated him and his sons and all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "At the same time we took all his cities and utterly destroyed every
        city\u2014men, women and children. We left no survivor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'We took only the cattle as plunder for ourselves and the spoil of
        the cities which we had captured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From Aroer, which is on the edge of the Arnon Valley, and from the
        city which is in the valley, as far as Gilead, there was no city [whose wall
        was] too high and too strong for us; the Lord our God handed over everything
        to us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Only you did not go near the land of the sons of Ammon, all along
        the river Jabbok and the cities of the hill country, and wherever the Lord
        our God had forbidden us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conquests Recounted'
      title: Conquests Recounted
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThen we turned and went up the road toward Bashan, and at
        Edrei, Og king of Bashan, with all his people came out to meet us in battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u2018Do not fear him, for I have handed
        him over to you, him and all his people and his land; and you shall do to
        him just as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the Lord our God also handed over Og king of Bashan, and all his
        people, into our hand and we struck him until no survivor was left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We captured all his cities at that time; there was not a city which
        we did not take from them: sixty cities, the whole region of Argob, the kingdom
        of Og in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All these cities were fortified and unassailable with their high
        walls, gates, and bars; in addition, [there were] a very great number of
        unwalled villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "We utterly destroyed them, just as we did to Sihon king of Heshbon,
        utterly destroying every city\u2014the men, women, and children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But we took all the cattle and the spoil of the cities as plunder
        for ourselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSo we took the land at that time from the hand of the two kings
        [Sihon and Og] of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, from the valley
        of the Arnon to Mount Hermon "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '(the Sidonians call Hermon Sirion, and the Amorites call it Senir): '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "all the cities of the plain and all Gilead and all Bashan, as far
        as Salecah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '(For only Og king of Bashan was left of the remnant of the [giants
        known as the] Rephaim. Behold, his bed frame was a bed frame of iron; is
        it not in Rabbah of the Ammonites? It was nine cubits (12 ft.) long and four
        cubits (6 ft.) wide, using the cubit of a man [the forearm to the end of
        the middle finger].)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSo we took possession of this land at that time. I gave the
        territory from Aroer, which is by the valley of the Arnon, along with half
        of the hill country of Gilead and its cities to the Reubenites and to the
        Gadites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The rest of Gilead and all of Bashan, the kingdom of Og, I gave to
        the half-tribe of Manasseh, that is, all the region of Argob (concerning
        all Bashan, it is called the land of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jair the son (descendant) of Manasseh took all the region of Argob
        as far as the border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, that is Bashan,
        and called it after his own name, Havvoth (the villages of) Jair, as it is
        called to this day.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I gave Gilead to Machir [of Manasseh]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'To the Reubenites and Gadites I gave the territory from Gilead as
        far as the Valley of Arnon, with the middle of the Valley as a boundary,
        and as far as the Jabbok River, the boundary of the sons of Ammon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Arabah also, with the Jordan as its boundary, from Chinnereth
        (the Sea of Galilee) as far as the sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea (Dead
        Sea), at the foot of the slopes of Pisgah on the east.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThen I commanded you [Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh]
        at that time, saying, \u2018The Lord your God has given you this land to
        possess; all you who are brave men shall cross over [the Jordan] armed before
        your brothers, the sons of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But your wives and your children and your cattle\u2014I know that
        you have much livestock\u2014shall remain in your cities which I have given
        you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "until the Lord gives rest to your fellow countrymen as [He has] to
        you, and they also possess the land which the Lord your God has given them
        beyond the Jordan. Then each of you may return to the land (possession) which
        I have given to you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I commanded Joshua at that time, saying, \u2018Your eyes have seen
        everything that the Lord your God has done to these two kings [Sihon and
        Og]; so the Lord shall do the same to all the kingdoms into which you are
        about to cross. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do not fear them, for it is the Lord your God who is fighting for
        you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThen I pleaded with the Lord at that time [for His favor],
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018O Lord God, You have only begun to show Your servant Your greatness
        and Your mighty hand; for what god is there in heaven or on earth that can
        do such works and mighty acts (miracles) as Yours? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I pray, let me go over and see the good land that is beyond the Jordan,
        that good hill country [with Hermon] and Lebanon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But the Lord was angry with me because of you [and your rebellion
        at Meribah], and would not listen to me; and the Lord said to me, \u2018Enough!
        Speak to Me no longer about this matter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Go up to the top of [Mount] Pisgah and raise your eyes toward the
        west and north and south and east, and see it with your eyes, for you shall
        not cross this Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But command Joshua and encourage and strengthen him, for he shall
        go across and lead this people, and he will give them the land which you
        see as an inheritance.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So we stayed in the Valley opposite Beth-peor.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel Urged to Obey God\u2019s Law"
      title: "Israel Urged to Obey God\u2019s Law"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow, O Israel, listen and pay attention to the statutes and
        the judgments (God\u2019s legal decisions) which I am teaching you to do,
        so that you may live and go in and take possession of the land which the
        Lord, the God of your fathers, is giving you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall not add to the word which I am commanding you, nor take
        away from it, so that you may keep the commandments of the Lord your God
        which I am commanding you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your eyes have seen what the Lord did at Baal-peor; for all the men
        who followed [and participated in the worship of] Baal of Peor, the Lord
        your God destroyed them from among you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but you who held tightly to the Lord your God are alive today, every
        one of you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CLook, I have taught you statutes and judgments just as the
        Lord my God has commanded me, so that you may do them in the land which you
        are entering to possess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So keep and do them, for that is your wisdom and your understanding
        in the sight of the peoples who will hear all these statutes and say, \u2018Surely
        this great nation is a wise and understanding people.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For what great nation is there that has a god so near to it as the
        Lord our God [is to us] whenever we call on Him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Or what great nation has statutes and judgments so righteous (upright,
        just) as this whole law which I am placing before you today?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201COnly pay attention and watch yourselves closely so that you
        do not forget the things which your eyes have seen and they do not depart
        from your heart all the days of your life. Make them known to your children
        and your grandchildren [impressing these things on their mind and penetrating
        their heart with these truths]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "especially the day you stood before the Lord your God at Horeb (Mount
        Sinai), when the Lord said to me, \u2018Assemble the people to Me and I will
        let them hear My words, so that they may learn to fear Me [with awe-filled
        reverence and profound respect] all the days they live on the land, and so
        that they may teach their children.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You approached and stood at the foot of the mountain, and the mountain
        burned with fire to the [very] heart of the heavens: darkness, cloud and
        thick gloom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord spoke to you from the midst of the fire; you heard
        the sound of the words, but you saw no form\u2014there was only a voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So He declared to you His covenant which He commanded you to follow,
        the Ten Commandments; and He wrote them on two tablets of stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Lord commanded me at that time to teach you the statutes and
        judgments, so that you might do them in the land which you are going over
        to possess.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSo pay attention and watch yourselves carefully\u2014for you
        did not see any form [of God] on the day the Lord spoke to you at Horeb from
        the midst of the fire\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'so that you do not act corruptly and make for yourselves a carved
        or sculpted image [to worship] in the form of any figure, the likeness of
        male or female, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the likeness of any animal that is on the earth, or of any winged
        bird that flies in the sky, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the likeness of anything that crawls on the ground, or of any fish
        that is in the waters beneath the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And beware that you do not raise your eyes toward heaven and see
        the sun and the moon and the stars, all the host of heaven, and let yourselves
        be led astray and worship them and serve them, [mere created bodies] which
        the Lord your God has allotted to [serve and benefit] all the peoples under
        the whole heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But the Lord has taken you and brought you out of the iron [smelting]
        furnace, out of Egypt, to be a people for His own possession, as [you are]
        this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNow the Lord was angry with me [at the waters of Meribah] because
        of you, and He swore [an oath] that I would not cross the Jordan, and that
        I would not enter the good land which the Lord your God is giving you as
        an inheritance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I am going to die in this land, I am not going to cross the Jordan,
        but you shall cross over and take possession of this good land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So be on your guard and watch yourselves, so that you do not forget
        the covenant of the Lord your God which He has made with you, and make for
        yourselves a carved or sculpted image in the form of anything which the Lord
        your God has forbidden you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For the Lord your God is a consuming fire; He is a jealous (impassioned)
        God [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely His].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWhen you become the father of children and grandchildren and
        have grown old in the land, then if you corrupt yourselves by making a carved
        or sculpted image in the form of anything [for the purpose of worship], and
        do evil [things] in the sight of the Lord your God, provoking Him to anger, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I call heaven and earth as witnesses against you today, that you
        will soon utterly perish from the land which you are crossing the Jordan
        to possess. You shall not live long on it, but will be utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The Lord will scatter and disperse you among the peoples (pagan nations),
        and you will be left few in number among the nations where the Lord drives
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And there you will serve [false and foreign] gods, the work of human
        hands, [lifeless images of] wood and stone, which neither see nor hear nor
        eat nor smell [the offerings of food given to them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But from there you will seek the Lord your God, and you will find
        Him if you search for Him with all your heart and all your soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When you are in distress and tribulation and all these things come
        on you, in the latter days you will return to the Lord your God and listen
        to His voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the Lord your God is a merciful and compassionate God; He will
        not fail you, nor destroy you, nor forget the covenant with your fathers
        which He swore to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CIndeed, ask now about the days that are past, [those days]
        which were before you, since the day that God created man on the earth, and
        ask from one end of the heavens to the other. Has anything been done like
        this great thing, or has anything been heard like it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Did [any] people ever hear the voice of God speaking out of the midst
        of the fire, as you heard, and [still] live? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Or has any [man-made] god ever tried to go and take for himself a
        nation from within another nation by trials, by signs and wonders and by
        war and by a mighty hand and by an outstretched arm and by great terrors,
        as the Lord your God did for you in Egypt before your [very] eyes? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'It was shown to you so that you might have [personal] knowledge and
        comprehend that the Lord is God; there is no other besides Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Out of the heavens He let you hear His voice to discipline and admonish
        you; and on earth He let you see His great fire, and you heard His words
        from the midst of the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And because He loved your fathers, He chose their descendants who
        followed them, and brought you from Egypt with His Presence, with His great
        and awesome power, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'dispossessing and driving out from before you nations, [nations that
        were] greater and mightier than you, to bring you in, to give you their land
        as an inheritance, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Therefore know and understand today, and take it to your heart, that
        the Lord is God in the heavens above and on the earth below; there is no
        other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So you shall keep His statutes and His commandments which I am commanding
        you today, so that it may go well with you and with your children after you,
        and so that you may live long on the land which the Lord your God is giving
        you for all time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then Moses set apart three cities [of refuge] beyond the Jordan toward
        the rising of the sun (eastward), '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'so that someone who committed manslaughter could flee there, [that
        is, a person] who killed his neighbor unintentionally and without previously
        having hostility toward him, and that by escaping to one of these cities
        he might [claim the right of asylum and] save his life: '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Bezer in the wilderness on the plateau for the Reubenites, and Ramoth
        in Gilead for the Gadites, and Golan in Bashan for the Manassites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'This is the law which Moses placed before the sons of Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'these are the testimonies (legal provisions) and the statutes and
        the judgments which Moses spoke to the sons of Israel when they came out
        of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'beyond the Jordan in the Valley opposite Beth-peor, in the land of
        Sihon king of the Amorites who lived at Heshbon, whom Moses and the sons
        of Israel defeated when they came out from Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'They took possession of his land and the land of Og king of Bashan,
        the two kings of the Amorites, who reigned across the Jordan to the east, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'from Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley of the [river] Arnon,
        as far as Mount Sion (that is, Hermon), '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: with all the Arabah (desert lowlands) across the Jordan to the east,
        even as far as the sea of the Arabah (the Dead Sea), at the foot of the slopes
        of Pisgah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ten Commandments Repeated'
      title: The Ten Commandments Repeated
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Moses summoned all Israel and said to them:\u201CHear, O Israel,
        the statutes and judgments (legal decisions) which I am speaking today in
        your hearing, so that you may learn them and observe them carefully. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord our God made a covenant with us at Horeb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord did not make this covenant with our fathers, but with us,
        all of us who are alive here today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord spoke with you face to face at the mountain from the midst
        of the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I was standing between the Lord and you at that time, to declare
        to you the word of the Lord; for you were afraid because of the fire and
        did not go up the mountain. He said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018I am the Lord your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt,
        out of the house of slavery.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018You shall have no other gods before Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018You shall not make for yourself an idol [as an object to worship],
        or any likeness (form, manifestation) of what is in heaven above or on the
        earth beneath or in the water under the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall not worship them or serve them; for I, the Lord your God,
        am a jealous (impassioned) God [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely
        mine], visiting (avenging) the iniquity (sin, guilt) of the fathers on the
        children [that is, calling the children to account for the sins of their
        fathers], to the third and the fourth generations of those who hate Me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but showing graciousness and lovingkindness to thousands [of generations]
        of those who love Me and keep My commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u2018You shall not take the name of the Lord your God in vain [that
        is, irreverently, in false affirmations or in ways that impugn the character
        of God]; for the Lord will not hold guiltless nor leave unpunished the one
        who takes His name in vain [disregarding its reverence and its power].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018Observe the Sabbath day to keep it holy (set apart, dedicated
        to God), as the Lord your God commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Six days you shall labor and do all your work, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but the seventh day is a Sabbath [a day of rest dedicated] to the
        Lord your God; on that day you shall not do any work, you or your son or
        your daughter or your male servant or your female servant or your ox or your
        donkey or any of your livestock or the stranger who stays inside your [city]
        gates, so that your male servant and your female servant may rest as well
        as you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall remember [with thoughtful concern] that you were a slave
        in the land of Egypt, and that the Lord your God brought you out of there
        with a mighty hand and by an outstretched arm; therefore the Lord your God
        has commanded you to observe the Sabbath day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Honor (respect, obey, care for) your father and your mother,
        as the Lord your God has commanded you, so that your days [on the earth]
        may be prolonged and so that it may go well with you in the land which the
        Lord your God gives you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018You shall not murder.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018You shall not commit adultery.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018You shall not steal.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018You shall not give false testimony [that is, lie, withhold,
        or manipulate the truth] against your neighbor (any person).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Moses Interceded'
      title: Moses Interceded
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018You shall not covet [that is, desire and seek to acquire] your
        neighbor\u2019s wife, nor desire your neighbor\u2019s house, his field, his
        male servant or his female servant, his ox or his donkey or anything that
        belongs to your neighbor.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe Lord spoke these words with a great voice to all your assembly
        at the mountain out of the midst of the fire, the cloud, and the thick darkness,
        and He added no more. He wrote these commandments on two tablets of stone
        and gave them to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And when you heard the voice from the midst of the darkness, while
        the mountain was burning with fire, you approached me, all the leaders (heads)
        of your tribes and your elders; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and you said, \u2018Behold, the Lord our God has shown us His glory
        and His greatness, and we have heard His voice from the midst of the fire;
        we have seen today that God speaks with man, yet he [still] lives. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now then why should we die? For this great fire will consume us;
        if we hear the voice of the Lord our God any longer, then we will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For who is there of all flesh (mankind) who has heard the voice of
        the living God speaking from the midst of the fire, as we have, and lived? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "You, Moses, go near and listen to everything that the Lord our God
        says; then speak to us everything that the Lord our God speaks to you, and
        we will listen and do it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThe Lord heard your words when you spoke to me, and the Lord
        said to me, \u2018I have heard the words of this people which they have spoken
        to you. They have done well in all that they have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Oh that they had such a heart in them, that they would fear [and
        worship Me with awe-filled reverence and profound respect] and keep all My
        commandments always, so that it may go well with them and with their children
        forever! '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Go and say to them, \u201CReturn to your tents.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But as for you, stand here by Me, and I will tell you all the commandments
        and the statutes and the judgments which you shall teach them, so that they
        may obey them in the land which I give them to possess.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Therefore you shall pay attention and be careful to do just as the
        Lord your God has commanded you; you shall not turn aside to the right or
        to the left [deviating from My commandments]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: You shall walk [that is, live each and every day] in all the ways
        which the Lord your God has commanded you, so that you may live and so that
        it may be well with you, and that you may live long in the land which you
        will possess.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Obey God and Prosper'
      title: Obey God and Prosper
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow this is the command; the statutes and the judgments (precepts)
        which the Lord your God has commanded me to teach you, so that you might
        do (follow, obey) them in the land which you are crossing over [the Jordan]
        to possess, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'so that you and your son and your grandson may fear and worship the
        Lord your God [with awe-filled reverence and profound respect], to keep [and
        actively do] all His statutes and His commandments which I am commanding
        you, all the days of your life, so that your days may be prolonged. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore listen, O Israel, and be careful to do them, that it may
        go well with you and that you may increase greatly [in numbers], as the Lord,
        the God of your fathers, has promised you, in a land flowing with milk and
        honey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CHear, O Israel! The Lord is our God, the Lord is one [the only
        God]! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart and mind and
        with all your soul and with all your strength [your entire being]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'These words, which I am commanding you today, shall be [written]
        on your heart and mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You shall teach them diligently to your children [impressing God\u2019s
        precepts on their minds and penetrating their hearts with His truths] and
        shall speak of them when you sit in your house and when you walk on the road
        and when you lie down and when you get up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you shall bind them as a sign on your hand (forearm), and they
        shall be used as bands (frontals, frontlets) on your forehead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen it shall come about when the Lord your God brings you
        into the land which He swore (solemnly promised) to [give] your fathers\u2014to
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob\u2014to give you, [a land with] great and splendid
        cities which you did not build, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and houses full of all good things which you did not fill, and hewn
        (excavated) cisterns (wells) which you did not dig out, and vineyards and
        olive trees which you did not plant, and you eat and are full and satisfied, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then beware that you do not forget the Lord who brought you out of
        the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall fear [only] the Lord your God; and you shall serve Him
        [with awe-filled reverence and profound respect] and swear [oaths] by His
        name [alone]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall not follow other gods, any of the gods of the peoples who
        surround you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "for the Lord your God who is among you is a jealous (impassioned)
        God [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely His]\u2014otherwise the anger
        of the Lord your God will be kindled and burn against you, and He will destroy
        you from the face of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYou shall not put the Lord your God to the test, as you tested
        Him at Massah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall diligently keep [foremost in your thoughts and actively
        do] the commandments of the Lord your God, and His testimonies and His statutes
        which He has commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You shall do what is right and good in the sight of the Lord, so
        that it may be well with you and that you may go in and possess the good
        land which the Lord swore to [give] your fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'by driving out all your enemies from before you, as the Lord has
        spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhen your son asks you in time to come, saying, \u2018What
        is the meaning of the testimonies and statutes and judgments (precepts) which
        the Lord our God has commanded you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "then you shall say to your son, \u2018We were Pharaoh\u2019s slaves
        in Egypt, and the Lord brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Moreover, the Lord showed great and terrible signs and wonders before
        our eyes against Egypt, Pharaoh and all his household; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He brought us out from there in order to bring us in, to give us
        the land which He had sworn to [give] our fathers.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the Lord commanded us to do all these statutes, to fear [and worship]
        the Lord our God [with awe-filled reverence and profound respect] for our
        good always and so that He might preserve us alive, as it is today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "It will be [considered] righteousness for us [that is, right standing
        with God] if we are careful to observe all this commandment before the Lord
        our God\u2014just as He has commanded us."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warnings'
      title: Warnings
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen the Lord your God brings you into the land which you
        are entering to possess, and has cleared away many nations before you, the
        Hittite and the Girgashite and the Amorite and the Canaanite and the Perizzite
        and the Hivite and the Jebusite, seven nations greater and mightier than
        you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and when the Lord your God gives them over to you and you defeat
        them, then you shall utterly destroy them. You shall not make a covenant
        (treaty) with them nor show mercy and compassion to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall not intermarry with them; you shall not give your daughter
        to his son, nor shall you take his daughter for your son; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for they will turn your sons away from following Me to serve other
        gods; then the anger of the Lord will be kindled and burn against you and
        He will quickly destroy you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But this is how you shall deal with them: you shall tear down their
        altars and smash to pieces their sacred pillars, and cut down their Asherim
        (symbols of the goddess Asherah), and burn their carved or sculpted images
        in the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you are a holy people [set apart] to the Lord your God; the Lord
        your God has chosen you out of all the peoples on the face of the earth to
        be a people for His own possession [that is, His very special treasure].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThe Lord did not love you and choose you because you were greater
        in number than any of the other peoples, for you were the fewest of all peoples. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But because the Lord loves you and is keeping the oath which He swore
        to your fathers, the Lord has brought you out with a mighty hand and redeemed
        (bought) you from the house of slavery, from the hand of Pharaoh king of
        Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore know [without any doubt] and understand that the Lord your
        God, He is God, the faithful God, who is keeping His covenant and His [steadfast]
        lovingkindness to a thousand generations with those who love Him and keep
        His commandments; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but repays those who hate Him to their faces, by destroying them;
        He will not hesitate with him who hates Him, He will repay him to his face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Promises of God'
      title: Promises of God
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, you shall keep (follow, obey) the commandment and the
        statutes and judgments (precepts) which I am commanding you today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThen it shall come about, because you listen to these judgments
        and keep and do them, that the Lord your God will keep with you the covenant
        and the [steadfast] lovingkindness which He swore to your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will love you and bless you and multiply you; He will also bless
        the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your land, your grain and your new
        wine and your [olive] oil, the offspring of your cattle and the young of
        your flock, in the land which He swore to your fathers to give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall be blessed above all peoples; there will be no male or
        female barren (childless, infertile) among you or among your cattle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Lord will take away from you all sickness; and He will not subject
        you to any of the harmful diseases of Egypt which you have known, but He
        will impose them on all [those] who hate you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And you shall consume all the peoples whom the Lord your God will
        give over to you; your eye shall not pity them, nor shall you serve their
        gods, for that would be a [deadly] trap to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CIf you say in your heart, \u2018These nations are greater than
        I am; how can I dispossess them?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "you shall not be afraid of them; you shall remember [with confidence]
        what the Lord your God did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the great trials which you saw with your own eyes, and the signs,
        the wonders, the mighty hand and the outstretched arm by which the Lord your
        God brought you out. So shall the Lord your God do to all the peoples of
        whom you are afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Moreover, the Lord your God will send the hornet (His terror) against
        them, until those who are left and hide themselves from you perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall not dread them, for the Lord your God is in your midst,
        a great and awesome God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Lord your God will clear away these nations before you little
        by little; you will not be able to put an end to them quickly, for [if you
        did] the wild animals would become too numerous for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the Lord your God will hand them over to you, and will confuse
        them with a great panic until they are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And He will hand over their kings to you, and you will make their
        name perish from under heaven; no man will be able to stand before you until
        you have destroyed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall burn the carved and sculpted images of their gods in the
        fire. You shall not covet the silver or gold that is on them, nor take it
        for yourselves, so that you will not be ensnared by it [in a deadly trap],
        for it is an abomination (repulsive) to the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: You shall not bring an abomination (idol) into your house, and like
        it come under the ban (doomed to destruction); you shall utterly detest and
        you shall utterly hate it, for it is something banned.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Gracious Dealings"
      title: "God\u2019s Gracious Dealings"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CEvery commandment that I am commanding you today you shall
        be careful to do, so that you may live and multiply, and go in and possess
        the land which the Lord swore [to give] to your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And you shall remember [always] all the ways which the Lord your
        God has led you these forty years in the wilderness, so that He might humble
        you and test you, to know what was in your heart (mind), whether you would
        keep His commandments or not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He humbled you and allowed you to be hungry and fed you with manna,
        [a substance] which you did not know, nor did your fathers know, so that
        He might make you understand [by personal experience] that man does not live
        by bread alone, but man lives by every word that proceeds out of the mouth
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Your clothing did not wear out on you, nor did your feet swell these
        forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore, know in your heart (be fully cognizant) that the Lord
        your God disciplines and instructs you just as a man disciplines and instructs
        his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, you shall keep the commandments of the Lord your God,
        to walk [that is, to live each and every day] in His ways and fear [and worship]
        Him [with awe-filled reverence and profound respect]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the Lord your God is bringing you into a good land, a land of
        brooks of water, of fountains and springs, flowing forth in valleys and hills; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'a land of wheat and barley, and vines and fig trees and pomegranates,
        a land of olive oil and honey; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'a land where you will eat bread without shortage, in which you will
        lack nothing; a land whose stones are iron, and out of whose hills you can
        dig copper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When you have eaten and are satisfied, then you shall bless the Lord
        your God for the good land which He has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBeware that you do not forget the Lord your God by failing
        to keep His commandments and His judgments (precepts) and His statutes which
        I am commanding you today; "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'otherwise, when you have eaten and are satisfied, and have built
        good houses and lived in them,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and when your herds and flocks multiply, and your silver and gold
        multiply, and all that you have increases, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then your heart will become lifted up [by self-conceit and arrogance]
        and you will forget the Lord your God who brought you from the land of Egypt,
        out of the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He led you through the great and terrible wilderness, with its fiery
        serpents and scorpions and thirsty ground where there was no water; it was
        He who brought water for you out of the flinty rock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He fed you manna in the wilderness, [a substance] which your fathers
        did not know, so that He might humble you [by dependence on Him] and that
        He might test you, to do good [things] for you at the end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Otherwise, you may say in your heart, \u2018My power and the strength
        of my hand made me this wealth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But you shall remember [with profound respect] the Lord your God,
        for it is He who is giving you power to make wealth, that He may confirm
        His covenant which He swore (solemnly promised) to your fathers, as it is
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it shall come about if you ever forget the Lord your God and
        follow other gods and serve them and worship them, I testify against you
        today that you will most certainly perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Like the nations which the Lord causes to perish before you, so shall
        you perish; because you would not listen to and obey the voice of the Lord
        your God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Provoked God'
      title: Israel Provoked God
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHear, O Israel! You are crossing the Jordan today to go in
        to dispossess nations greater and more powerful than you, great cities fortified
        to heaven, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "a people great and tall, sons of Anakim, whom you know and of whom
        you have heard it said, \u2018Who can stand before the sons of Anak?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So know today [with confident assurance] that the Lord your God is
        crossing [the Jordan] before you like a devouring fire. He will destroy them
        and He will subdue them before you, and you shall drive them out and destroy
        them quickly, just as the Lord has promised you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CDo not say in your heart when the Lord your God has driven
        them out before you, \u2018Because of my righteousness the Lord has brought
        me in to possess this land,\u2019 but because of the wickedness of these
        nations the Lord is dispossessing them before you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It is not for your righteousness or for the uprightness of your heart
        that you are going to possess their land, but because of the wickedness of
        these nations the Lord your God is driving them out before you, and to confirm
        the oath which the Lord swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CKnow [without any doubt], that the Lord your God is not giving
        you this good land to possess because of your righteousness, for you are
        a stiff-necked (stubborn, obstinate) people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember [with remorse] and do not forget how you provoked the Lord
        your God to wrath in the wilderness; from the day you left the land of Egypt
        until you arrived in this place, you have been rebellious against the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And at Horeb (Sinai) you provoked the Lord to wrath, and the Lord
        was so angry with you that He would have destroyed you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When I went up the mountain to receive the tablets of stone, the
        tablets of the covenant which the Lord made with you, I remained on the mountain
        forty days and forty nights; I did not eat food or drink water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord gave me the two tablets of stone written with the finger
        of God; and on them were written all the words which the Lord had spoken
        to you at the mountain from the midst of the fire on the day of the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'It came about at the end of forty days and forty nights that the
        Lord gave me the two tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u2018Arise, go down from here quickly,
        for your people whom you brought from Egypt have acted corruptly. They have
        quickly turned aside from the way which I commanded them; they have made
        (cast) a molten image for themselves.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Furthermore, the Lord said to me, \u2018I have seen this people,
        and indeed, they are stiff-necked (stubborn, obstinate) people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Let Me alone, so that I may destroy them and wipe out their name
        from under heaven; and I will make of you a nation mightier and greater than
        they.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSo I turned and came down from the mountain while the mountain
        was burning with fire, and the two tablets of the covenant were in my two
        hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I saw that you had indeed sinned against the Lord your God. You
        had made for yourselves a molten calf (idol). You had turned aside quickly
        from the way which the Lord had commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So I took hold of the two tablets and threw them from my two hands
        and smashed them before your very eyes! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then, as before, I fell down before the Lord for [another] forty
        days and forty nights; I did not eat food or drink water, because of all
        the sin you had committed by doing what was evil in the sight of the Lord
        to provoke Him to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For I was afraid of the anger and absolute fury which the Lord held
        against you, [enough divine fury] to destroy you, but the Lord listened to
        me that time also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Lord was very angry with Aaron, angry [enough] to destroy him,
        so I also prayed for Aaron at the same time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I took your sinful thing, the calf which you had made, and burned
        it in the fire and thoroughly crushed it, grinding the metal thoroughly until
        it was as fine as dust; and I threw its dust into the brook that came down
        from the mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAt Taberah also and at Massah and at Kibroth-hattaavah you
        provoked the Lord to wrath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And when the Lord sent you from Kadesh-barnea, saying, \u2018Go up
        and take possession of the land which I have given you,\u2019 then you rebelled
        against the command of the Lord your God, and you did not believe and rely
        on Him, nor did you obey His voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have been rebellious against the Lord from the [first] day that
        I knew you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CSo I fell down and lay face down before the Lord forty days
        and nights because the Lord had said He would destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then I prayed to the Lord and said, \u2018O Lord God, do not destroy
        Your people, even Your inheritance, whom You have redeemed through Your greatness,
        whom You have brought from Egypt with a mighty hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Remember [with compassion] Your servants, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob;
        do not look at the stubbornness of this people or at their wickedness or
        at their sin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "so that the [people of the] land from which You brought us will not
        say, \u201CBecause the Lord was not capable of bringing them into the land
        which He had promised them and because He hated them He has brought them
        out to the wilderness [in order] to kill them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Yet they are Your people and Your inheritance, whom You have brought
        out by Your great power and by Your outstretched arm.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tablets Rewritten'
      title: The Tablets Rewritten
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt that time the Lord said to me, \u2018Cut out for yourself
        two tablets of stone like the first, and come up to Me on the mountain, and
        make an ark (chest) of wood for yourself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first tablets
        which you shattered, and you shall put them in the ark.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I made an ark of acacia wood and cut out two tablets of stone
        like the first, and went up the mountain with the two tablets in my hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord wrote on the tablets, like the first writing, the Ten Commandments
        which the Lord had spoken to you on the mountain from the midst of the fire
        on the day of the assembly; then the Lord gave them to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I turned and came down from the mountain and put the tablets
        in the ark which I had made; and they are there, just as the Lord commanded
        me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(Now the sons of Israel traveled from the wells of the sons of Jaakan
        to Moserah. There Aaron died and there he was buried and Eleazar his son
        ministered as priest in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'From there they traveled to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah,
        a land of brooks of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At that time the Lord set apart the tribe of Levi to carry the ark
        of the covenant of the Lord, to stand before the Lord to serve Him and to
        bless in His name until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore, Levi does not have a portion or inheritance [of tribal
        land] with his brothers; the Lord is his inheritance, as the Lord your God
        has promised him.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd I stayed on the mountain, like the first time, forty days
        and nights, and the Lord listened to me at that time also; the Lord was not
        willing to destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u2018Arise, go on your journey ahead of
        the people, so that they may go in and take possession of the land which
        I swore to their fathers to give to them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd now, Israel, what does the Lord your God require from you,
        but to fear [and worship] the Lord your God [with awe-filled reverence and
        profound respect], to walk [that is, to live each and every day] in all His
        ways and to love Him, and to serve the Lord your God with all your heart
        and with all your soul [your choices, your thoughts, your whole being], "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and to keep the commandments of the Lord and His statutes which I
        am commanding you today for your good? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Behold, the heavens and the highest of heavens belong to the Lord
        your God, the earth and all that is in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yet the Lord  had a delight in loving your fathers and set His affection
        on them, and He chose their descendants after them, you above all peoples,
        as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So circumcise [that is, remove sin from] your heart, and be stiff-necked
        (stubborn, obstinate) no longer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the Lord your God is the God of gods and the Lord of lords, the
        great, the mighty, the awesome God who does not show partiality nor take
        a bribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He executes justice for the orphan and the widow, and shows His love
        for the stranger (resident alien, foreigner) by giving him food and clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore, show your love for the stranger, for you were strangers
        in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall fear [and worship] the Lord your God [with awe-filled reverence
        and profound respect]; you shall serve Him and cling to Him [hold tightly
        to Him, be united with Him], and you shall swear [oaths] by His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He is your praise and glory; He is your God, who has done for you
        these great and awesome things which you have seen with your own eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Your fathers went down to Egypt, seventy persons [in all], and now
        the Lord your God has made you as numerous as the stars of heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rewards of Obedience'
      title: Rewards of Obedience
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CTherefore you shall love the Lord your God, and always keep
        His charge, His statutes, His precepts, and His commandments [it is your
        obligation to Him]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Know this day that I am not speaking to your children who have not
        known [by personal experience] and who have not seen [firsthand] the instruction
        and discipline of the Lord your God\u2014His greatness, His mighty hand and
        His outstretched arm; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and His signs and His works which He did in the midst of Egypt to
        Pharaoh the king of Egypt and to all his land; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and what He did to the army of Egypt, to its horses and its chariots,
        when He made the water of the Red Sea engulf them as they pursued you, and
        how the Lord  completely destroyed them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and what He did to you in the wilderness until you came to this place; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and what He did to Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, the son
        of Reuben, when the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them, their households,
        their tents, and every living thing that followed them, in the midst of all
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For your eyes have seen all the great work of the Lord which He did.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore, you shall keep all the commandments which I am commanding
        you today, so that you may be strong and go in and take possession of the
        land which you are crossing over [the Jordan] to possess; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'so that you may live long on the land which the Lord swore (solemnly
        promised) to your fathers to give to them and to their descendants, a land
        [of great abundance,] flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the land which you are entering to possess is not like the land
        of Egypt from which you have come, where you sowed your seed and watered
        it with your foot like a garden of vegetables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the land into which you are about to cross to possess, a land
        of hills and valleys, drinks water from the rain of heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'a land for which the Lord your God cares; the eyes of the Lord your
        God are always on it, from the beginning of the year to the end of the year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIt shall come about, if you listen obediently and pay attention
        to My commandments which I command you today\u2014to love the Lord your God
        and to serve Him with all your heart and with all your soul [your choices,
        your thoughts, your whole being]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'that He will give the rain for your land in its season, the early
        [fall] rain and the late [spring] rain, so that you may gather in your grain
        and your new wine and your [olive] oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And He will give grass in your fields for your cattle, and you will
        eat and be satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Beware that your hearts are not deceived, and that you do not turn
        away [from the Lord] and serve other gods and worship them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "or [else] the Lord\u2019s anger will be kindled and burn against
        you, and He will shut up the heavens so that there will be no rain and the
        land will not yield its fruit; and you will perish quickly from the good
        land which the Lord is giving you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CTherefore, you shall impress these words of mine on your heart
        and on your soul, and tie them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be
        as bands (frontals, frontlets) on your forehead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You shall teach them [diligently] to your children [impressing God\u2019s
        precepts on their minds and penetrating their hearts with His truths], speaking
        of them when you sit in your house and when you walk along the road and when
        you lie down and when you rise up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'so that your days and the days of your children may be multiplied
        in the land which the Lord swore to your fathers to give them, as long as
        the heavens are above the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For if you are careful to keep all this commandment which I am commanding
        you to do, to love the Lord your God, to walk [that is, to live each and
        every day] in all His ways and to hold tightly to Him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'then the Lord will drive out all these nations from before you, and
        you shall dispossess nations greater and mightier than you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Every place on which the sole of your foot treads shall become yours;
        your territory shall be from the wilderness to Lebanon, and from the river,
        the river Euphrates, as far as the western sea (the Mediterranean). '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'No man will be able to stand before you; the Lord your God will lay
        the fear and the dread of you on all the land on which you set foot, just
        as He has spoken to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBehold, today I am setting before you a blessing and a curse\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the blessing, if you listen to and obey the commandments of the Lord
        your God, which I am commanding you today; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and the curse, if you do not listen to and obey the commandments
        of the Lord your God, but turn aside from the way which I am commanding you
        today, by following (acknowledging, worshiping) other gods which you have
        not known.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIt shall come about, when the Lord your God brings you into
        the land which you are entering to possess, that you shall place the blessing
        on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Are they not across the Jordan, west of the road, toward the sunset,
        in the land of the Canaanites who live in the Arabah, opposite Gilgal, beside
        the oaks of Moreh? '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For you are about to cross the Jordan to go in to possess the land
        which the Lord your God is giving you, and you shall possess it and live
        in it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: and you shall be careful to do all the statutes and the judgments
        which I am setting before you today.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Laws of the Sanctuary'
      title: Laws of the Sanctuary
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThese are the statutes and judgments (precepts) which you
        shall be careful to do in the land which the Lord, the God of your fathers,
        has given you to possess as long as you live on the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall utterly destroy all the places where the nations whom you
        shall dispossess serve their gods, on the high mountains and the hills and
        under every green [leafy] tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall tear down their altars and smash their [idolatrous] pillars
        and burn their Asherim in the fire; you shall cut down the carved and sculpted
        images of their gods and obliterate their name from that place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall not act like this toward the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But you shall seek the Lord at the place which the Lord your God
        will choose out of all your tribes to establish His Name there for His dwelling
        [place], and there you shall come [to worship Him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There you shall bring your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your
        tithes, the contribution of your hand, your votive (pledged, vowed) offerings,
        your freewill (voluntary) offerings, and the firstborn of your herd and of
        your flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And there you and your households shall eat before the Lord your
        God, and rejoice in all to which you put your hand, in which the Lord your
        God has blessed you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CYou shall not do at all what we are doing here [in the camp]
        today, every man doing whatever is right in his [own] eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For you have not yet come to the resting place and to the inheritance
        which the Lord your God is giving you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When you cross the Jordan and live in the land which the Lord your
        God is giving you to inherit, and He gives you rest from all your enemies
        around you so that you live in security, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'then it shall come about that the place which the Lord your God will
        choose for His Name [and Presence] to dwell; there you shall bring everything
        that I am commanding you: your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your tithes
        and the [voluntary] contribution of your hand [as a first gift from the fruits
        of the ground], and all your choice votive offerings which you vow to the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you shall rejoice before the Lord your God, you and your sons
        and your daughters, and your male and female servants, and the Levite who
        is within your [city] gates, since he has no portion or inheritance with
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBe careful that you do not offer your burnt offerings in every
        [cultic] place you see, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but [only] in the place which the Lord will choose in one of your
        tribes, there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there you shall do
        everything that I am commanding you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CHowever, you may slaughter and eat meat within any of your
        [city] gates, whatever you wish, according to the blessing of the Lord your
        God which He has given you [as His generous provision for daily life]. The
        [ceremonially] unclean and the clean may eat it, such as the gazelle and
        the deer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Only you shall not eat the blood; you are to pour it out on the ground
        like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You are forbidden to eat within your [city] gates the tithe of your
        grain or new wine or oil, or the firstborn of your herd or flock, or any
        of your votive offerings, or your freewill offerings, or the contribution
        of your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But you shall eat them before the Lord your God in the place which
        the Lord your God will choose, you and your son and your daughter, and your
        male and female servants, and the Levite who is within your [city] gates;
        and you shall rejoice before the Lord your God in all that you undertake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Be careful that you do not neglect the Levite [who serves God] as
        long as you live in your land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhen the Lord your God extends your territory, as He promised
        you, and you say, \u2018I will eat meat,\u2019 because you want to eat meat,
        then you may eat meat, whatever you wish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If the place which the Lord your God chooses to put His Name (Presence)
        is too far away from you, then you may slaughter [animals] from your herd
        or flock which the Lord has given you, just as I have commanded you; and
        you may eat within your [city] gates whatever you wish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Just as the gazelle or the deer is eaten, so you may eat it [but
        not make it an offering]; the [ceremonially] unclean and the clean alike
        may eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Only be sure that you do not eat the blood, for the blood is the
        life (soul), and you shall not eat the life with the meat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall not eat it; you shall pour it out on the ground like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall not eat it, so that all may be well with you and with your
        children after you, because you will be doing what is right in the sight
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'However, you shall take your holy things which you have [to offer]
        and your votive (pledged, vowed) offerings, you shall take them and go to
        the place which the Lord will choose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And you shall offer your burnt offerings, the meat and the blood,
        on the altar of the Lord your God; and the blood of your sacrifices shall
        be poured out on the altar of the Lord your God, and you shall eat the meat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CBe careful to listen to all these words which I am commanding
        you, so that it may be well with you and with your children after you forever,
        because you will be doing what is good and right in the sight of the Lord
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWhen the Lord your God cuts off and destroys before you the
        nations which you are going in to dispossess, and you dispossess them and
        settle in their land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "beware that you are not lured (ensnared) into following them, after
        they have been destroyed before you, and that you do not inquire about their
        gods, saying, \u2018How did these nations serve their gods, so that I too
        may do likewise?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'You shall not behave this way toward the Lord your God, for they
        have done for their gods every repulsive thing which the Lord hates; for
        they even burn their sons and their daughters in the fire [as sacrifices]
        to their gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CEverything I command you, you shall be careful to do it; you
        shall not add to it nor take away from it."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Shun Idolatry'
      title: Shun Idolatry
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf a prophet arises among you, or a dreamer of dreams, and
        gives you a sign or a wonder, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and the sign or the wonder which he spoke (foretold) to you comes
        to pass, and if he says, \u2018Let us follow after other gods (whom you have
        not known) and let us serve and worship them,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'you shall not listen to the words of that prophet or that dreamer
        of dreams; for the Lord your God is testing you to know whether you love
        the Lord your God with all your heart and mind and all your soul [your entire
        being]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall walk after the Lord your God and you shall fear [and worship]
        Him [with awe-filled reverence and profound respect], and you shall keep
        His commandments and you shall listen to His voice, and you shall serve Him,
        and cling to Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But that prophet or that dreamer of dreams shall be put to death,
        because he has counseled rebellion against the Lord your God who brought
        you from the land of Egypt and redeemed you from the house of slavery, to
        draw you away from the way in which the Lord your God has commanded you to
        walk. So you shall remove the evil from among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf your brother, the son of your mother, or your son or daughter,
        or the wife you cherish, or your friend who is as [precious to you as] your
        own life (soul), entices you secretly, saying, \u2018Let us go and serve
        other gods\u2019 (gods whom neither you nor your fathers have known, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'of the gods of the peoples who are around you, near you or far from
        you, from one end of the earth to the other), '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'you shall not consent to him or listen to him; and your eye shall
        not pity him, nor shall you spare him or conceal him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Instead, you shall most certainly execute him; your hand shall be
        first [to be raised] against him to put him to death, and afterwards the
        hand of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So you shall stone him to death with stones, because he has tried
        to draw you away from the Lord your God who brought you from the land of
        Egypt, from the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then all Israel will hear and be afraid, and will never again do
        such a wicked thing among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf you hear [it said] in one of your cities, which the Lord
        your God gives you to live in, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "that some worthless and evil men have gone out from among you and
        have tempted the inhabitants of their city [to sin], saying, \u2018Let us
        go and serve other gods\u2019 (whom you have not known), "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then you shall investigate and search out [witnesses] and ask thorough
        questions. If it is true and the matter is established that this loathsome
        thing has been done among you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'you shall most certainly strike the inhabitants of that city with
        the edge of the sword, utterly destroying it and all that is in it, even
        its livestock with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then you shall collect all its spoil (plunder) into the middle of
        its open square and burn the city and set fire to the spoil as a whole burnt
        offering to the Lord your God. It shall be a ruin forever. It shall not be
        built again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Nothing from that which is put under the ban (designated for destruction)
        shall cling to your hand, so that the Lord may turn away from His burning
        anger and show mercy to you, and have compassion on you and make you increase,
        just as He swore to your fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: because you have listened to and obeyed the voice of the Lord your
        God, keeping all His commandments which I am commanding you today, and doing
        what is right in the eyes of the Lord your God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Clean and Unclean Animals'
      title: Clean and Unclean Animals
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou are the sons of the Lord your God; you shall not cut
        yourselves nor shave your forehead for the sake of the dead, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for you are a holy people [set apart] to the Lord your God; and the
        Lord has chosen you out of all the peoples who are on the earth to be a people
        for His own possession.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou shall not eat anything that is detestable [to the Lord
        and forbidden by Him]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These are the animals that you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the deer, the gazelle, the roebuck, the wild goat, the ibex, the
        antelope and the mountain sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Among the animals, you may eat any animal that has the divided hoof
        [that is, a hoof] split into two parts [especially at its distal extremity]
        and that chews the cud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'However, you are not to eat any of these [animals] among those which
        chew the cud, or among those that divide the hoof in two: the camel, the
        hare and the shaphan, for though they chew the cud, they do not split the
        hoof; they are unclean for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The swine, because it has a divided hoof but does not chew the cud;
        it is unclean for you. You shall not eat their meat nor touch their carcasses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201COf all [creatures] that are in the waters, you may eat these:
        anything that has fins and scales you may eat, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but you may not eat anything that does not have fins and scales;
        it is unclean for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou may eat any clean bird. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But these are the ones which you shall not eat: the eagle, the vulture,
        and the black buzzard, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and the red kite, the falcon, and the birds of prey of any variety, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and every raven of any variety, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the ostrich, the owl, the seagull, the hawk of any variety, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the little owl, the great owl, the long-eared owl, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the pelican, the carrion vulture, the cormorant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the stork, and the heron of any variety, and the hoopoe, and the
        bat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And all flying insects are unclean for you; they shall not be eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You may eat any clean bird.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall not eat anything that dies on its own. You may give
        it to the stranger (resident alien, foreigner) who is in your [city] gates,
        so that he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner [since they are
        not under God\u2019s law], but you are a people holy (set apart) to the Lord
        your God. You shall not boil a young goat or a lamb in its mother\u2019s
        milk.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CEvery year you shall certainly tithe [a tenth] of all the yield
        of your seed which is produced by your field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You shall eat the tithe (tenth) of your grain, your new wine, your
        oil, and the firstborn of your herd and your flock before the Lord your God
        in the place where He chooses to establish His Name (Presence), so that you
        may learn to fear [and worship] the Lord your God [with awe-filled reverence
        and profound respect] always. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If the place where the Lord your God chooses to set His Name (Presence)
        is a great distance from you and you are not able to carry your tithe, because
        the Lord your God has blessed you [with such an abundance], '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then you shall exchange your tithe for money, and take the money
        in your hand and go to the place [of worship] which the Lord your God chooses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You may spend the money for anything your heart desires: for oxen,
        or sheep, or wine, or [other] strong drink, or anything else you want. You
        shall eat there in the presence of the Lord your God and rejoice, you and
        your household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Also you shall not neglect the Levite who is within your [city] gates,
        for he does not have a share [of land] or an inheritance among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAt the end of every third year you shall bring out all the
        tithe of your produce for that year, and shall store it up within your [city]
        gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The Levite, because he has no share [of land] or an inheritance among
        you, and the stranger, and the orphan and the widow who are within your [city]
        gates, shall come and eat and be satisfied, so that the Lord your God may
        bless you in all the work of your hands.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sabbatical Year'
      title: The Sabbatical Year
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt the end of every seven years you shall grant a release
        (remission, pardon) from debt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is the regulation for the release: every creditor shall forgive
        what he has loaned to his neighbor; he shall not require repayment from his
        neighbor and his brother, because the Lord\u2019s release has been proclaimed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You may require repayment from a foreigner, but whatever of yours
        is with your brother [Israelite] your hand shall release. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'However, there will be no poor among you, since the Lord will most
        certainly bless you in the land which the Lord your God is giving you as
        an inheritance to possess, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'if only you will listen to and obey the voice of the Lord your God,
        to observe carefully all these commandments which I am commanding you today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the Lord your God blesses you as He has promised you, then you
        will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow; and you will rule over
        many nations, but they will not rule over you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf there is a poor man among you, one of your fellow Israelites,
        in any of your cities in the land that the Lord your God is giving you, you
        shall not be heartless, nor close-fisted with your poor brother; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but you shall freely open your hand to him, and shall generously
        lend to him whatever he needs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Beware that there is no wicked thought in your heart, saying, \u2018The
        seventh year, the year of release (remission, pardon), is approaching,\u2019
        and your eye is hostile (unsympathetic) toward your poor brother, and you
        give him nothing [since he would not have to repay you]; for he may cry out
        to the Lord against you, and it will become a sin for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall freely and generously give to him, and your heart shall
        not be resentful when you give to him, because for this [generous] thing
        the Lord your God will bless you in all your work and in all your undertakings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the poor will never cease to be in the land; therefore I command
        you, saying, \u2018You shall freely open your hand to your brother, to your
        needy, and to your poor in your land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf your fellow Israelite, a Hebrew man or woman, is sold to
        you, and serves you for six years, then in the seventh year you shall set
        him free [from your service]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When you set him free, you shall not let him go away empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall give him generous provisions from your flock, from your
        threshing floor and from your wine press; you shall give to him as the Lord
        your God has blessed you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And you shall remember and thoughtfully consider that you were [once]
        a slave in the land of Egypt, and the Lord your God redeemed you; therefore,
        I am commanding you these things today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now if the servant says to you, \u2018I will not leave you,\u2019
        because he loves you and your household, since he is doing well with you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then take an awl and pierce it through his ear into the door, and
        he shall [willingly] be your servant always. Also you shall do the same for
        your maidservant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIt shall not seem hard to you when you set him free, for he
        has served you six years with double the service of a hired man; so the Lord
        your God will bless you in everything you do.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou shall consecrate (set apart) to the Lord your God all the
        firstborn males that are born of your herd and flock. You shall not work
        with the firstborn of your herd, nor shear the firstborn of your flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You and your household shall eat it every year before the Lord your
        God in the place [for worship] which the Lord chooses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if it has any defect or injury, such as lameness or blindness,
        or any serious defect, you shall not sacrifice it to the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall eat it within your [city] gates; the [ceremonially] unclean
        and the clean alike may eat it, as [if it were] a gazelle or a deer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Only you shall not eat its blood; you are to pour it out on the ground
        like water.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Feast of Passover'
      title: The Feast of Passover
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CObserve the month of Abib and celebrate the Passover to the
        Lord your God, for in the month of Abib the Lord your God brought you out
        of Egypt by night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall sacrifice the Passover [lamb] to the Lord your God from
        the flock or the herd, in the place where the Lord chooses to establish His
        Name (Presence). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall not eat leavened bread with it; instead, for seven days
        you shall eat the Passover with unleavened bread, the bread of affliction
        (for you left the land of Egypt in haste); [do this] so that all the days
        of your life you may remember [thoughtfully] the day when you came out of
        the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For seven days no leaven shall be seen with you in all your territory,
        and none of the meat which you sacrificed the evening of the first day shall
        remain overnight until morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You are not allowed to sacrifice the Passover [lamb] in any of your
        cities which the Lord your God is giving you; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but at the place where the Lord your God chooses to establish His
        Name (Presence), you shall sacrifice the Passover [lamb] in the evening at
        sunset, at the time that you came out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall cook and eat it in the place which the Lord your God chooses.
        In the morning you are to return to your tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Feast of Weeks'
      title: The Feast of Weeks
      number: 8
      content: 'For six days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day
        there shall be a celebration to the Lord your God; so you shall do no work
        [on that day].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall count seven weeks for yourself; you shall begin to
        count seven weeks from the time you first put the sickle to the standing
        grain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then you shall celebrate the Feast of Weeks to the Lord your God
        with a tribute of a freewill offering from your hand, which you shall give
        [to Him] just as the Lord your God blesses you; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you shall rejoice before the Lord your God, you and your son
        and your daughter and your male and female servants and the Levite who is
        within your [city] gates, and the stranger and the orphan and the widow who
        are among you, at the place where the Lord your God chooses to establish
        His Name (Presence). '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Feast of Booths'
      title: The Feast of Booths
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and you shall
        be careful to obey these statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall celebrate the Feast of Booths (Tabernacles) seven
        days, when you have gathered in [the grain] from your threshing floor and
        [the wine] from your wine vat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall rejoice in your feast, you and your son and your daughter
        and your male and female servants and the Levite and the stranger and the
        orphan and the widow who are within your city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Seven days you shall celebrate a feast to the Lord your God in the
        place which the Lord chooses, because the Lord your God will bless you in
        all your produce and in all the work of your hands, so that you will be altogether
        joyful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThree times a year all your males shall appear before the Lord
        your God in the place which He chooses, at the Feast of Unleavened Bread
        (Passover) and at the Feast of Weeks (Pentecost) and at the Feast of Booths
        (Tabernacles), and they shall not appear before the Lord empty-handed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Every man shall give as he is able, in accordance with the blessing
        which the Lord your God has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall appoint judges and officers in all your cities (gates)
        which the Lord your God is giving you, according to your tribes, and they
        shall judge the people with righteous judgment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You shall not distort justice; you shall not be partial, and you
        shall not take a bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of the wise and perverts
        the words of the righteous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall pursue justice, and only justice [that which is uncompromisingly
        righteous], so that you may live and take possession of the land which the
        Lord your God is giving you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall not plant for yourself an Asherah of any kind of
        tree or wood beside the altar of the Lord your God, which you shall make. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You shall not set up for yourself a sacred pillar which the Lord your
        God hates.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Administration of Justice'
      title: Administration of Justice
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not sacrifice to the Lord your God an ox or sheep
        with a blemish or any defect, for that is a detestable thing to the Lord
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf there is discovered among you, within any of your cities,
        which the Lord your God is giving you, a man or a woman who does evil in
        the sight of the Lord your God, by transgressing (violating) His covenant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and has gone and served other gods and worshiped them, or the sun
        or the moon or any of the heavenly host, [doing these things] which I have
        commanded not to do, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and if it is told to you and you hear about it, then you shall investigate
        thoroughly [all the charges]. If it is confirmed beyond doubt that this detestable
        thing has been done in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then you shall bring that man or that woman who has done this evil
        thing to the gates [of your city] and you shall stone the man or the woman
        to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On the evidence of two or three witnesses, he who is to die shall
        be put to death; he shall not be put to death on the evidence of [only] one
        witness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The hand of the witnesses shall be the first against him to put him
        to death, and afterward the hand of all the people. So you shall remove the
        evil from among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIf any case is too difficult for you to judge\u2014between
        one kind of homicide and another, between one kind of lawsuit and another,
        between one kind of assault and another, being controversial issues in your
        courts\u2014then you shall arise and go to the place which the Lord your
        God chooses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So you shall come to the Levitical priests or to the judge who is
        in office at that time, and you shall consult them and they will declare
        to you the verdict in the case. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall act in accordance with the terms of the verdict which they
        declare to you from that place which the Lord chooses. You shall be careful
        to act in accordance with all of their instructions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall act in accordance with the law which they teach you and
        the judgment which they tell you. You shall not turn aside from their verdict,
        to the right or to the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The man who acts presumptuously and insolently by not listening to
        the priest who stands there to serve the Lord your God, nor to the judge,
        that man shall die; so you shall remove the evil from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then all the people will hear and be afraid, and will not act presumptuously
        again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhen you enter the land which the Lord your God is giving you,
        and you take possession of it and live there, and you say, \u2018I will set
        a king over me like all the nations who are around me,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'you shall most certainly set a king over you whom the Lord your God
        chooses. You shall set a king over you from among your countrymen (brothers);
        you may not choose a foreigner [to rule] over you who is not your countryman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Further, he shall not acquire many [war] horses for himself, nor
        make the people return to Egypt in order to acquire horses [to expand his
        military power], since the Lord said to you, \u2018You shall never return
        that way again.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He shall not acquire multiple wives for himself, or else his heart
        will turn away [from God]; nor [for the same reason] shall he acquire great
        amounts of silver and gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CNow it shall come about when he sits on the throne of his kingdom,
        he shall write for himself a copy of this law on a scroll in the presence
        of the Levitical priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it shall be with him and he shall read it all the days of his
        life, so that he may learn to fear [and worship] the Lord his God [with awe-filled
        reverence and profound respect], by carefully obeying (keeping foremost in
        his thoughts and actively doing) all the words of this law and these statutes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: so that his heart will not be lifted up above his countrymen [by a
        false sense of self-importance and self-reliance] and that he will not turn
        away (deviate) from the commandment, to the right or to the left, so that
        he and his sons may continue [to reign] for a long time in his kingdom in
        Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Portion of the Levites'
      title: Portion of the Levites
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThe Levitical priests, the entire tribe of Levi, shall own
        [privately] no portion [of land] or inheritance with Israel; they shall eat
        the Lord\u2019s offerings by fire and His portion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They shall have no inheritance [of land] among their countrymen (brothers,
        brethren); the Lord is their inheritance, as He promised them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CNow this shall be the priests\u2019 portion from the people,
        from those offering a sacrifice, either an ox or a sheep: they shall give
        to the priest the shoulder and the two cheeks and the stomach. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall also give him the first fruits of your grain, your new
        wine [the first of the season], and your [olive] oil, and the first sheared
        fleece of your sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the Lord your God has chosen him, him and his sons from all your
        tribes, to stand and serve in the name of the Lord forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNow if a Levite comes from any of your cities throughout Israel
        where he resides, and comes whenever he wishes to [the sanctuary] the place
        which the Lord chooses; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then he shall serve in the name of the Lord his God, like all his
        fellow Levites who stand there before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Spiritism Forbidden'
      title: Spiritism Forbidden
      number: 8
      content: "They shall have equal portions to eat, except what they receive from
        the sale of their fathers\u2019 estates.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen you enter the land which the Lord your God is giving you,
        you shall not learn to imitate the detestable (repulsive) practices of those
        nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'There shall not be found among you anyone who makes his son or daughter
        pass through the fire [as a sacrifice], one who uses divination and fortune-telling,
        one who practices witchcraft, or one who interprets omens, or a sorcerer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'or one who casts a charm or spell, or a medium, or a spiritist, or
        a necromancer [who seeks the dead]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For everyone who does these things is utterly repulsive to the Lord;
        and because of these detestable practices the Lord your God is driving them
        out before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall be blameless (complete, perfect) before the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For these nations which you shall dispossess listen to those who
        practice witchcraft and to diviners and fortune-tellers, but as for you,
        the Lord your God has not allowed you to do so.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThe Lord your God will raise up for you a prophet like me [Moses]
        from among you, from your countrymen (brothers, brethren). You shall listen
        to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This is according to all that you asked of the Lord your God at Horeb
        (Mount Sinai) on the day of the assembly, saying, \u2018Let me not hear the
        voice of the Lord my God again, nor see this great fire anymore, so that
        I will not die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Lord said to me, \u2018They have spoken well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will raise up a prophet from among their countrymen like you, and
        I will put My words in his mouth, and he shall speak to them all that I command
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'It shall come about that whoever will not listen to My words which
        he shall speak in My name, I Myself will require it of him [and there will
        be consequences]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the prophet who presumes to speak a word in My name which I have
        not commanded him to speak, or which he speaks in the name of other gods\u2014that
        prophet shall die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "If you say in your heart, \u2018How will we know and recognize the
        word which the Lord has not spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: When a prophet speaks in the name of the Lord and the thing does not
        happen or come true, that is the thing which the Lord has not spoken. The
        prophet has spoken it presumptuously; you shall not be afraid of him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cities of Refuge'
      title: Cities of Refuge
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen the Lord your God cuts off (destroys) the nations whose
        land He is giving you, and you dispossess them and live in their cities and
        in their houses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'you shall designate three cities for yourself in the central area
        of the land, which the Lord your God is giving you to possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall prepare and maintain for yourself the roads [to these cities],
        and divide the territory of your land into three parts, so that anyone who
        kills another unintentionally may escape there [for asylum].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CNow this is the case of the offender (manslayer) who may escape
        there and live [protected from vengeance]: when he kills his neighbor unintentionally,
        not having hated him previously\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "as [for example] when a man goes into the forest with his neighbor
        to cut wood, and his hand swings the axe to cut down the tree, but the iron
        head slips off the wooden handle and hits his companion and he dies\u2014the
        offender may escape to one of these cities and live; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'otherwise the avenger of blood might pursue the offender in the heat
        of anger, and overtake him, because it is a long way, and take his life,
        even though he did not deserve to die, since he did not hate his neighbor
        beforehand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, I command you, saying, \u2018You shall set aside three
        cities [of refuge] for yourself.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIf the Lord your God enlarges your border, as He has sworn
        to your fathers to do, and gives you all the land which He promised to give
        to your fathers\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "if you keep and carefully observe all these commandments which I
        am commanding you today, to love the Lord your God, and to walk [that is,
        to live each and every day] always in His ways\u2014then you shall add three
        more cities [of refuge] for yourself, besides these three, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'so that innocent blood will not be shed [by blood avengers] in your
        land which the Lord your God is giving you as an inheritance, and blood guilt
        will not be on you [for the death of an innocent man].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBut if there is a man who hates his neighbor and lies in wait
        and ambush for him and attacks him and strikes him down so that he dies,
        and the assailant escapes to one of these cities, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then the elders of his own city shall send for him and have him taken
        back from there and turn him over to the avenger of blood, so that he may
        be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Laws of Landmark and Testimony'
      title: Laws of Landmark and Testimony
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall not pity him [the guilty one], but you shall purge the
        blood of the innocent from Israel, so that it may go well with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not move your neighbor\u2019s boundary mark, which
        the forefathers [who first divided the territory] have set, in the land which
        you will inherit in the land which the Lord your God is giving you to possess.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CA single witness shall not appear in a trial against a man
        for any wrong or any sin which he has committed; [only] on the testimony
        or evidence of two or three witnesses shall a charge be confirmed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If a malicious witness rises up against a man to [falsely] accuse
        him of wrongdoing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then both parties to the controversy shall stand before the Lord,
        before the priests and the judges who will be in office at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The judges shall investigate thoroughly, and if the witness is a
        false witness, and he has accused his brother falsely, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'then you shall do to him just as he had intended to do to his brother.
        So you shall remove the evil from among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Those who remain will hear and be afraid, and will never again do
        such an evil thing among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall not show pity [to the guilty one]: it shall be life for
        life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Laws of Warfare'
      title: Laws of Warfare
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen you go out to battle against your enemies and see horses
        and chariots and people more numerous than you, do not be afraid of them;
        for the Lord your God, who brought you up from the land of Egypt, is with
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When you approach the battle, the priest shall come forward and speak
        to the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and shall say to them, \u2018Hear, O Israel: you are advancing today
        to battle against your enemies. Do not lack courage. Do not be afraid, or
        panic, or tremble [in terror] before them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "for the Lord your God is He who goes with you, to fight for you against
        your enemies, to save you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The officers shall also speak to the soldiers, saying, \u2018What
        man is there who has built a new house and has not yet dedicated it? Let
        him go and return to his house, otherwise he might die in the battle and
        another man would dedicate it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'What man has planted a vineyard and has not put it to use [harvesting
        its fruit]? Let him go and return to his house, otherwise he might die in
        the battle and another man would begin to use its fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And who is the man who is engaged (legally promised) to a woman and
        has not married her? Let him go and return to his house, otherwise he might
        die in the battle and another man would marry her.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the officers shall speak further to the soldiers and say, \u2018Who
        is the man who is afraid and lacks courage? Let him go and return to his
        house, so that he does not cause his brothers\u2019 courage to fail like
        his own.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall be when the officers have finished speaking to the soldiers,
        they shall appoint commanders of armies over them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you advance to a city to fight against it, you shall [first]
        offer it terms of peace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'If that city accepts your terms of peace and opens its gates to you,
        then all the people who are found in it shall become your forced labor and
        shall serve you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'However, if it does not make peace with you, but makes war against
        you, then you shall lay siege to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When the Lord your God gives it into your hand, you shall strike
        down all the men in it with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Only the women and the children and the animals and everything that
        is in the city, all its spoil, you shall take as plunder for yourself; and
        you shall use the spoil of your enemies which the Lord your God has given
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'That is what you shall do to all the cities that are very far away
        from you, which are not among the cities of these nations nearby [which you
        are to dispossess]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Only in the cities of these peoples that the Lord your God is giving
        you as an inheritance, you shall not leave alive anything that breathes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But you shall utterly destroy them, the Hittite, the Amorite, the
        Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite, just as the Lord your
        God has commanded you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that they will not teach you to act in accordance with all the
        detestable practices which they have done [in worship and service] for their
        gods, and in this way cause you to sin against the Lord your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhen you besiege a city for a long time, making war against
        it in order to capture it, you shall not destroy its [fruit-bearing] trees
        by swinging an axe against them; for you may eat from them, and you shall
        not cut them down. For is the tree of the field a man, that it should be
        besieged (destroyed) by you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Only the trees which you know are not fruit trees shall you destroy
        and cut down, so that you may build siegeworks against the city that is making
        war with you until it falls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Expiation of a Crime'
      title: Expiation of a Crime
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf someone is found slain, lying in the field, in the land
        which the Lord your God gives you to possess, and it is not known who has
        killed him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then your elders and judges shall go out and measure the distance
        to the cities which are around the dead person. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It shall be that the elders of the city which is nearest to the dead
        man shall take a heifer of the herd, one which has not been worked and which
        has not pulled in a yoke; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and the elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a [river]
        valley with running water, which has not been plowed or planted, and shall
        break the heifer\u2019s neck there in the valley. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the priests, the sons of Levi, shall approach, for the Lord
        your God has chosen them to serve Him and to bless in the Name (Presence)
        of the Lord; and every dispute and every assault (violent crime) shall be
        settled by them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All the elders of that city nearest to the dead man shall wash their
        hands over the heifer whose neck was broken in the valley; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and they shall respond, and say, \u2018Our hands did not shed this
        blood, nor did our eyes see it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Forgive Your people Israel whom You have redeemed, O Lord, and do
        not put the guilt of innocent blood among Your people Israel.\u2019 And the
        guilt of blood shall be forgiven them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Domestic Relations'
      title: Domestic Relations
      number: 9
      content: 'So shall you remove the guilt of innocent blood from among you, when
        you do what is right in the sight of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you go out to battle against your enemies, and the Lord
        your God hands them over to you and you lead them away captive, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you see a beautiful woman among the captives, and desire her
        and would take her as your wife, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then you shall bring her [home] to your house, and she shall shave
        her head and trim her nails [in preparation for mourning]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She shall take off the clothes of her captivity and remain in your
        house, and weep (mourn) for her father and her mother a full month. After
        that you may go in to her and be her husband and she shall be your wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But it shall be that if you have no delight and take no pleasure
        in her, then you shall let her go wherever she wishes. You certainly shall
        not sell her for money; you shall not deal with her as a slave or mistreat
        her, because you have humbled her [by forced marriage].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf a man has two wives, one loved and the other unloved, and
        both the loved and the unloved have born him sons, and the firstborn son
        belongs to the unloved wife,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "then on the day when he wills his possessions to his sons, he cannot
        treat the son of his loved wife as firstborn in place of the son of the unloved
        wife\u2014the [actual] firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Instead he shall acknowledge the son of the unloved as the firstborn,
        by giving him a double portion of all that he has, for he was the beginning
        of his strength (generative power); to him belongs the right of the firstborn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf any man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not obey
        the voice of his father or of his mother, and when they reprimand and discipline
        him, he will not listen to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'then his father and mother shall take hold of him, and bring him
        out to the elders of his city at the gateway of his hometown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "They shall say to the elders of his city, \u2018This son of ours
        is stubborn and rebellious; he will not obey us, he is a glutton and a drunkard.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then all the men of his city shall stone him to death; so you shall
        remove the evil from among you, and all Israel will hear of it and be afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man has committed a sin worthy of death, and he is
        put to death and [afterward] you hang him on a tree [as a public example], "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: his body shall not hang all night on the tree, but you shall most
        certainly bury him on the same day (for he who is hanged is cursed by God),
        so that you do not defile your land which the Lord your God gives you as
        an inheritance.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Various Laws'
      title: Various Laws
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not see your countryman\u2019s ox or his sheep
        straying away or being stolen, and ignore [your duty to help] them; you shall
        certainly take them back to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'If your countryman is not nearby or you do not know him, you shall
        bring the animal to your house, and it shall stay with you until he searches
        for it; then you shall return it to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall do this with his donkey or with his garment or with anything
        that your countryman has lost and you have found. You are not allowed to
        ignore [your duty to help] them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall not see your countryman\u2019s donkey or his ox fall down
        along the road, and ignore [your duty to help] them; you shall certainly
        help him lift it up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CA woman shall not wear a man\u2019s clothing, nor shall a man
        put on a woman\u2019s clothing; for whoever does these things is utterly
        repulsive to the Lord your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf you happen to come upon a bird\u2019s nest along the road,
        in any tree or on the ground, with young ones or eggs, and the mother [bird]
        is sitting on the young or on the eggs, you shall not take the mother with
        the young. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall certainly let the mother go, but you may take the young
        for yourself, so that it may be well with you and that you may prolong your
        days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWhen you build a new house, you shall make a railing (parapet)
        around your [flat] roof, so that you do not bring the guilt of [innocent]
        blood on your house if someone falls from it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall not sow your vineyard with two kinds of seed, or
        everything produced by the seed which you have sown and the yield of the
        vineyard will become defiled [and banned for use].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall not plow with an ox [a clean animal] and a donkey
        [an unclean animal] together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou shall not wear a fabric made of wool and linen blended
        together [a fabric pagans believed to be magical].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Laws on Morality'
      title: Laws on Morality
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou shall make tassels for yourself on the four corners of
        your outer garment with which you cover yourself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf any man takes a wife and goes in to her and then scorns
        and hates her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and charges her [without cause] with shameful behavior and publicly
        defames her, and says, \u2018I took this woman, but when I approached her,
        I did not find in her evidence of virginity,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "then the young woman\u2019s father and her mother shall get and bring
        out the evidence of her virginity to the elders of the city at the gate [where
        court is held]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The father of the young woman shall say to the elders, \u2018I gave
        my daughter to this man as a wife, but he hates her and has turned against
        her; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and behold, he has made baseless charges against her, saying, \u201CI
        did not find in your daughter the evidence of her virginity.\u201D But this
        is the evidence of my daughter\u2019s virginity.\u2019 And they shall spread
        out the garment before the elders of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the elders of that city shall take the man and reprimand him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and they shall fine him a hundred shekels of silver and give it to
        the father of the young woman, because he publicly defamed a virgin of Israel.
        And she shall remain his wife; he is not allowed to divorce her as long as
        he lives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBut if this charge is true that the evidence of virginity was
        not found in the young woman, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "then they shall bring her out to the doorway of her father\u2019s
        house, and the men of her city shall stone her to death because she has committed
        a deliberate sin in Israel by playing the prostitute in her father\u2019s
        house. So you shall remove the evil from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf a man is intimate with a woman who is another man\u2019s
        wife, they shall both be put to death, the man who lay with the woman, and
        the woman. So you shall remove the evil from Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CIf a young woman who is a virgin is engaged (legally betrothed)
        to a man, and another man finds her in the city and is intimate with her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "then you shall bring them both out to the gate of that city and stone
        them to death\u2014the young woman because she did not cry out for help [though
        she was] in the city, and the man because he has violated his neighbor\u2019s
        [promised] wife. So you shall remove the evil from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CHowever, if the man finds the girl who is engaged (legally
        betrothed) in the [open] field, and seizes her and is intimate with her [by
        force], then only the man who lies with her shall be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But you shall do nothing to the young woman; she has committed no
        sin worthy of death, for this is the same as when a man attacks his neighbor
        and murders him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When he found her in the [open] field, the engaged girl [may have]
        cried out for help, but there was no one to [hear and] save her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIf a man finds a girl who is a virgin, who is not engaged,
        and seizes her and is intimate with her and they are discovered, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "then the man who was intimate with her shall give fifty shekels of
        silver to the girl\u2019s father, and she shall become his wife because he
        has violated her; he can never divorce her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CA man shall not take his father\u2019s [former] wife, so that
        he will not expose his father\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Persons Excluded from the Assembly'
      title: Persons Excluded from the Assembly
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHe who has been castrated by having his testicles crushed
        or his male organ cut off shall not enter the congregation of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A person of illegitimate birth shall not enter the assembly of the
        Lord; none of his descendants, even to the tenth generation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'An Ammonite or Moabite shall not enter the assembly of the Lord;
        none of their descendants, even to the tenth generation, shall ever enter
        the assembly of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'because they did not meet you with bread (food) and water on the
        road as you came out of Egypt, and because they hired [to act] against you
        Balaam the son of Beor from Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Nevertheless, the Lord your God was not willing to listen to Balaam,
        but the Lord your God turned the curse into a blessing for you because the
        Lord your God has loved you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall never seek their peace nor their prosperity all your days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall not detest an Edomite, for he is your brother [Esau\u2019s
        descendant]. You shall not detest an Egyptian, because you were a stranger
        (resident alien, foreigner) in his land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their children of the third generation who are born to them may enter
        the assembly of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen you go out as an army [to fight] against your enemies,
        you shall keep yourselves from every evil [thing].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf there is any man among you who is [ceremonially] unclean
        because of nocturnal emission, then he must go outside the camp; he shall
        not come back to the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when evening comes, he shall bathe in water, and at sundown he
        may return to the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou shall also have a place outside the camp to which you may
        go, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and you shall have a spade among your tools, and when you [prepare
        to] sit down outside [to relieve yourself], you shall dig a hole with it
        and shall turn and cover up your waste. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Since the Lord your God walks in the midst of your camp to rescue
        you and to defeat your enemies before you, therefore your camp must be holy
        (undefiled); and He must not see anything indecent among you or He will turn
        away from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYou shall not hand over to his master a slave who has escaped
        from his master to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He shall live among you, in the place he chooses in one of your cities
        where it pleases him; you shall not mistreat or oppress him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThere shall be no cult prostitute among the daughters of Israel,
        nor shall there be a cult prostitute (a sodomite) among the sons of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You shall not bring the wages of a prostitute or the price of a dog
        [that is, a male prostitute] into the house of the Lord your God as payment
        for any vow, for both of these [the gift and the giver] are utterly repulsive
        to the Lord your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou shall not charge interest to your fellow Israelite\u2014interest
        on money, food or anything that may be loaned for interest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You may charge interest to a foreigner, but to your fellow Israelite
        you shall not charge interest, so that the Lord your God may bless you in
        all that you undertake in the land which you are about to enter to possess.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CWhen you make a vow to the Lord your God, you shall not delay
        to pay it, for He will most certainly require it of you, and a delay would
        cause you to sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But if you refrain from making a vow, that would not be [counted
        as] sin in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You shall be careful to perform that [vow] which passes your lips,
        just as you have made a voluntary vow to the Lord your God, just as you have
        promised with your own words (mouth).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CWhen you enter your neighbor\u2019s vineyard, you may eat your
        fill of grapes, as many as you please, but you shall not put any in your
        basket [to take with you].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWhen you come into the standing grain of your neighbor, you
        may pluck the ears of grain with your hand, but you shall not wield a sickle
        in your neighbor\u2019s standing grain [to harvest it]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Law of Divorce'
      title: Law of Divorce
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen a man takes a wife and marries her, and it happens that
        she loses his favor because he has found something indecent or unacceptable
        about her, and he writes her a certificate of divorce, puts it in her hand
        and sends her out of his house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and after she leaves his house, she goes and becomes another man\u2019s
        wife, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and if the latter husband turns against her and writes her a certificate
        of divorce, puts it in her hand, and sends her out of his house, or if the
        latter husband dies who took her as his wife, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'then her former husband who [first] sent her away may not take her
        again as his wife, since she has been defiled; for that is an outrage before
        the Lord, and you shall not bring sin on the land which the Lord your God
        gives you as an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Various Laws'
      title: Various Laws
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhen a man takes a new wife, he shall not go out [to fight]
        with the army nor be charged with any duty; he shall be free at home for
        one year and shall bring happiness to his wife whom he has taken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNo one shall take a handmill or an upper millstone [used to
        grind grain into bread] as security [for a debt], for he would be taking
        a [person\u2019s] life in pledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf a man is caught kidnapping any of his countrymen from the
        sons of Israel, and he treats him violently or sells him [as a slave], then
        that thief shall die. So you shall remove the evil from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBe careful during an outbreak of leprosy, that you diligently
        observe and do according to all that the Levitical priests teach you; just
        as I have commanded them, so you shall be careful to do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Remember [with thoughtful concern] what the Lord your God did to
        Miriam on the road as you came out of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you lend your neighbor anything, you shall not go into
        his house to get his pledge (security deposit). "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall stand outside, and the man to whom you lend shall bring
        the pledge out to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If the man is poor, you shall not keep his pledge overnight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall certainly restore the pledge (security deposit) to him
        at sunset, so that he may sleep in his garment and bless you; and it will
        be credited to you as righteousness (right standing) before the Lord your
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take advantage of a hired servant who is poor
        and needy, whether [he is] one of your countrymen or one of the strangers
        (resident aliens, foreigners) who is in your land inside your cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "You shall give him his wages on the day that he earns them before
        the sun sets\u2014for he is poor and is counting on it\u2014so that he does
        not cry out to the Lord against you, and it becomes a sin for you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThe fathers shall not be put to death for [the sins of] their
        children, nor shall the children be put to death for their fathers; [only]
        for his own sin shall anyone be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall not pervert the justice due a stranger or an orphan,
        nor seize (impound) a widow\u2019s garment as security [for a loan]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and the Lord
        your God redeemed you from there; therefore I am commanding you to do this
        thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhen you reap your harvest in your field and have forgotten
        a sheaf [of grain] in the field, you shall not go back to get it; it shall
        be for the stranger, for the orphan, and for the widow, so that the Lord
        your God may bless you in all the work of your hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When you beat [the olives off of] your olive tree, do not search
        through the branches again; [whatever is left] shall be for the stranger,
        for the orphan, and for the widow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CWhen you gather the grapes of your vineyard, you shall not
        glean it afterward; it shall be for the stranger, for the orphan, and for
        the widow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You shall [thoughtfully] remember [the fact] that you were a slave
        in the land of Egypt; therefore I am commanding you to do this thing.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Various Laws'
      title: Various Laws
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf there is a controversy between men, and they go to court,
        and the judges decide [the issue] between them, and they judge in favor of
        the innocent and condemn the guilty, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then it shall be that if the guilty man deserves to be beaten, the
        judge shall make him lie down and be beaten in his presence with a [certain]
        number of stripes in proportion to his offense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He may have him beaten forty times, but no more. He is not to be
        beaten with more stripes than these and he is not to be degraded [that is,
        treated like an animal] in your sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall not muzzle the ox while he is threshing [to prevent
        him from eating any of the grain].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf brothers are living together and one of them dies without
        a son, the widow of the deceased shall not be married outside the family
        to a stranger. Her husband\u2019s brother shall be intimate with her after
        taking her as his wife and perform the duty of a husband\u2019s brother to
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'It shall be that her firstborn [son] will be given the name of the
        dead brother, so that his name will not be blotted out of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But if the man does not want to marry his brother\u2019s [widowed]
        wife, then she shall go up to the gate [of the city, where court is held]
        to the elders, and say, \u2018My brother-in-law refuses to continue his brother\u2019s
        name in Israel; he is not willing to perform the duty of a husband\u2019s
        brother.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the elders of his city will summon him and speak to him. And
        if he stands firm and says, \u2018I do not want to marry her,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "then his brother\u2019s widow shall approach him in the presence
        of the elders, and pull his sandal off his foot and spit in his face; and
        she shall answer and say, \u2018So it is done to that man who does not build
        up his brother\u2019s household.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In Israel his [family] name shall be, \u2018The house of him whose
        sandal was removed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIf [two] men, a man and his countryman, are fighting and the
        wife of one approaches to rescue her husband from the man who is striking
        him, and she reaches out with her hand and grabs the aggressor\u2019s genitals, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then you shall cut off her hand; you shall not show pity [for her].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall not have in your bag inaccurate weights, a heavy
        and a light [so you can cheat others]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall not have in your house inaccurate measures, a large and
        a small. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall have a perfect (full) and just weight, and a perfect and
        just measure, so that your days may be long in the land which the Lord your
        God gives you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For everyone who does such things, everyone who acts unjustly [without
        personal integrity] is utterly repulsive to the Lord your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CRemember what Amalek did to you along the road when you came
        from Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'how he met you along the road and attacked all the stragglers at
        your rear when you were tired and weary; and he did not fear God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Therefore when the Lord your God has given you rest from all your
        surrounding enemies, in the land which the Lord your God gives you as an
        inheritance to possess, you shall wipe out the memory of Amalek from under
        heaven; you must not forget.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offering First Fruits'
      title: Offering First Fruits
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThen it shall be, when you enter the land which the Lord
        your God gives you as an inheritance, and you take possession of it and live
        in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that you shall take some of the first of all the produce of the ground
        which you harvest from the land that the Lord your God gives you, and you
        shall put it in a basket and go to the place where the Lord your God chooses
        to establish His Name (Presence). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall go to the priest who is in office at that time and say
        to him, \u2018I declare this day to the Lord  my God that I have entered
        the land which the Lord swore to our fathers to give us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the priest will take the basket from you and place it before
        the altar of the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And you shall say before the Lord your God, \u2018My father [Jacob]
        was a wandering Aramean, and he [along with his family] went down to Egypt
        and lived there [as strangers], few in number; but while there he became
        a great, mighty and populous nation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Egyptians treated us badly and oppressed us, and imposed
        hard labor on us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then we cried out to the Lord, the God of our fathers for help, and
        He heard our voice and saw our suffering and our labor and our [cruel] oppression; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and the Lord brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand and with
        an outstretched arm and with great terror [suffered by the Egyptians] and
        with signs and with wonders; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and He has brought us to this place and has given us this land, a
        land flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And now, look, I have brought the first of the produce of the ground
        which You, O Lord, have given me.\u2019 And you shall place it before the
        Lord your God, and shall worship before the Lord your God; "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you and the Levite and the stranger (resident alien, foreigner)
        among you shall rejoice in all the good which the Lord your God has given
        you and your household.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you have finished paying all the tithe of your produce
        the third year, [which is] the year of tithing, then you shall give it to
        the Levite, to the stranger, to the orphan, and to the widow, so that they
        may eat within the gates of your cities and be satisfied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You shall say before the Lord your God, \u2018I have removed the
        sacred portion (the tithe) from my house and also have given it to the Levite,
        to the stranger, to the orphan, and to the widow, in accordance with all
        that You have commanded me. I have not transgressed or forgotten any of Your
        commandments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have not eaten from the tithe while mourning, nor have I removed
        any of it when I was [ceremonially] unclean [making the tithe ceremonially
        unclean], nor offered any of it to the dead. I have listened to the voice
        of the Lord my God; I have done everything in accordance with all that You
        have commanded me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Look down from Your holy dwelling above, from heaven, and bless Your
        people Israel, and the land which You have given us, as You have sworn to
        our fathers, a land [of plenty] flowing with milk and honey.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis day the Lord your God commands you to do these statutes
        and judgments (precepts). Therefore, you shall be careful to do them with
        all your heart and with all your soul (your entire being). "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Today you have [openly] declared the Lord to be your God, and that
        you will walk [that is, live each and every day] in His ways and keep His
        statutes, His commandments, and His judgments (precepts), and listen to His
        voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Today the Lord has declared that you are His people, His treasured
        possession, just as He promised you, and that you are to keep all His commandments; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and that He will set you high above all the nations which He has
        made, for praise, fame, and honor: and that you shall be a holy people [set
        apart and consecrated] to the Lord your God, just as He has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Altar at Mount Ebal'
      title: The Altar at Mount Ebal
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Moses and the elders of Israel commanded the people, saying,
        \u201CKeep (remember, obey) all the commandments which I am commanding you
        today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So it shall be on the day when you cross the Jordan to [enter] the
        land which the Lord your God gives you, that you shall set up for yourself
        large stones and coat them with plaster (lime, whitewash). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall write on the stones all the words of this law when you
        cross over, so that you may go into the land which the Lord your God gives
        you, a land [of plenty] flowing with milk and honey, just as the Lord, the
        God of your fathers has promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now when you cross the Jordan you shall set up these stones on Mount
        Ebal, just as I am commanding you today and coat them with plaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'There you shall build an altar to the Lord your God, an altar of
        stones; you shall not use an iron tool on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall build the altar of the Lord your God with whole [uncut]
        stones, and offer burnt offerings on it to the Lord your God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and you shall sacrifice peace offerings and shall eat there, and
        shall rejoice before the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And you shall write very clearly on the stones all the words of this
        law.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Moses and the Levitical priests said to all Israel, \u201CBe
        silent and listen, O Israel! This day you have become a people for the Lord
        your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Curses of Mount Ebal'
      title: The Curses of Mount Ebal
      number: 10
      content: "So you shall obey the voice of the Lord your God, and do His commandments
        and statutes which I am commanding you today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moses also commanded the people that day, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThese [tribes] shall stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people
        when you have crossed the Jordan: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph,
        and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'These [tribes] shall stand on Mount Ebal to pronounce the curse [for
        disobedience]: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Levites shall answer with a loud voice to all the men of Israel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u2018Cursed is the man who makes a carved or cast image (idol),
        a repulsive thing to the Lord, the work of the hands of the artisan, and
        sets it up in secret.\u2019 All the people shall answer and say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who dishonors (treats with contempt) his father
        or his mother.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who moves his neighbor\u2019s boundary mark.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who misleads a blind person on the road.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who distorts (perverts) the justice due to a stranger,
        an orphan, and a widow.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who is intimate with his father\u2019s [former]
        wife, because he has violated what belongs to his father.\u2019 And all the
        people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who is intimate with any animal.\u2019 And all
        the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who is intimate with his [half] sister, whether
        his father\u2019s or his mother\u2019s daughter.\u2019 And all the people
        shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who is intimate with his mother-in-law.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who strikes his neighbor in secret.\u2019 And
        all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who accepts a bribe to strike down an innocent
        person.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018Cursed is he who does not confirm the words of this law by
        doing them [keeping them, taking them to heart as the rule of his life].\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Blessings at Gerizim'
      title: Blessings at Gerizim
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow it shall be, if you diligently listen to and obey the
        voice of the Lord your God, being careful to do all of His commandments which
        I am commanding you today, the Lord your God will set you high above all
        the nations of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'All these blessings will come upon you and overtake you if you pay
        attention to the voice of the Lord your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou will be blessed in the city, and you will be blessed in
        the field.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThe offspring of your body and the produce of your ground and
        the offspring of your animals, the offspring of your herd and the young of
        your flock will be blessed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CYour basket and your kneading bowl will be blessed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou will be blessed when you come in and you will be blessed
        when you go out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThe Lord will cause the enemies who rise up against you to
        be defeated before you; they will come out against you one way, but flee
        before you seven ways. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord will command the blessing upon you in your storehouses and
        in all that you undertake, and He will bless you in the land which the Lord
        your God gives you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Lord will establish you as a people holy [and set apart] to Himself,
        just as He has sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of the Lord your
        God and walk [that is, live your life each and every day] in His ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So all the peoples of the earth will see that you are called by the
        name of the Lord, and they will be afraid of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord will give you great prosperity, in the offspring of your
        body and in the offspring of your livestock and the produce of your ground,
        in the land which the Lord swore to your fathers to give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Lord will open for you His good treasure house, the heavens,
        to give rain to your land in its season and to bless all the work of your
        hand; and you will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The Lord will make you the head (leader) and not the tail (follower);
        and you will be above only, and you will not be beneath, if you listen and
        pay attention to the commandments of the Lord your God, which I am commanding
        you today, to observe them carefully. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Consequences of Disobedience'
      title: Consequences of Disobedience
      number: 14
      content: 'Do not turn aside from any of the words which I am commanding you
        today, to the right or to the left, to follow and serve other gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut it shall come about, if you do not listen to and obey the
        voice of the Lord your God, being careful to do all His commandments and
        His statutes which I am commanding you today, then all these curses will
        come upon you and overtake you:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYou will be cursed in the city and cursed in the field.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYour basket and your kneading bowl will be cursed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe offspring of your body and the produce of your land, the
        offspring of your herd and the young of your flock will be cursed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou will be cursed when you come in and you will be cursed
        when you go out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe Lord will send upon you curses, confusion, and rebuke in
        everything that you undertake to do, until you are destroyed, perishing quickly
        because of the evil of your deeds, because you have turned away from Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Lord will make the pestilence and plague cling to you until He
        has consumed and eliminated you from the land which you are entering to possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Lord will strike you with consumption [causing you to waste away]
        and with fever and with inflammation and with fiery heat and with the sword
        and with blight and with mildew [on your crops]; and they will pursue you
        until you perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The heaven which is over your head shall be bronze [giving no rain
        and blocking all prayers], and the earth which is under you, iron [hard to
        plow and yielding no produce]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The Lord will make the rain of your land powder and dust; from heaven
        it will come down on you until you are destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThe Lord will cause you to be defeated before your enemies;
        you will go out against them one way, but flee before them seven ways, and
        you will be an example of terror to all the kingdoms of the earth [when they
        see your destruction]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Your carcasses will be food for all the birds of the sky and the
        beasts of the earth, and there will be no one to frighten them away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThe Lord will strike you with the boils of Egypt and with tumors
        and with the scab and the itch that you cannot heal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The Lord will strike you with madness and with blindness and with
        bewilderment of heart and mind; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and you will be groping at noon [in broad daylight], just as the
        blind grope in the darkness, and nothing you do will prosper; but you will
        only be oppressed and exploited and robbed continually, with no one to save
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You will be pledged to marry a wife, but another man will be intimate
        with her [before you]; you will build a house, but you will not live in it;
        you will plant a vineyard, but you will not use its fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Your ox will be slaughtered before your eyes, but you will not eat
        any of it; your donkey will be torn away from you, and it will not be returned
        to you; your sheep will be given to your enemies, and you will have no one
        to save you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Your sons and daughters will be given to another people, while your
        eyes look on and long for them continually; but there will be nothing you
        can do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'A people whom you do not know will eat the produce of your land and
        all the products of your labors, and you will never be anything but oppressed
        and exploited and crushed continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You shall be driven mad by the sight of the things you see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Lord will strike you on the knees and on the legs with sore boils
        that you cannot heal, from the sole of your foot to the crown of your head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The Lord will bring you and your king, whom you appoint over you,
        to a nation which you and your fathers have never known; there you will [be
        forced to] serve other gods, [lifeless gods of] wood and stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And you will become a horror, a proverb [a mere object lesson], and
        a taunt [a derisive joke] among all the people to which the Lord drives you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CYou will bring out a great quantity of seed to the field, but
        you will gather in little, because the locusts will consume it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'You will plant vineyards and cultivate them, but you will not drink
        the wine or gather the grapes, because the worm will eat them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'You will have olive trees throughout your territory but you will
        not anoint yourselves with the oil, because your olives will drop off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You will have sons and daughters, but they will not be yours [for
        long], because they will go into captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The cricket will take possession of all your trees and the produce
        of your ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The stranger who lives among you will rise above you higher and higher,
        and you will go down lower and lower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'He will lend to you [out of his affluence], but you will not lend
        to him [because of your poverty]; he will be the head, and you the tail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CSo all these curses will come on you and pursue you and overtake
        you until you are destroyed, because you would not obey the voice of the
        Lord your God by keeping His commandments and His statutes which He has commanded
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'They will be a sign and a wonder to you and your descendants forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CBecause you did not serve the Lord your God with a heart full
        of joy and gladness for the abundance of all things [with which He blessed
        you], "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'you will therefore serve your enemies whom the Lord sends against
        you, in hunger and in thirst, in nakedness and in lack of all things; and
        He will put an iron yoke [of slavery] on your neck until He has destroyed
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u201CThe Lord will bring a nation against you from far away, from
        the end of the earth, [as swift] as the eagle swoops down [to attack], a
        nation whose language you will not understand, "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'a defiant nation who will have no respect for the old, nor show favor
        to the young, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'and it will eat the offspring of your herd and the produce of your
        ground until you are destroyed, who will leave you no grain, new wine, or
        oil, nor the offspring of your herd or the young of your flock until they
        have caused you to perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'They will besiege you in all your cities until your high and fortified
        walls in which you trusted come down throughout your land; and they will
        besiege you in all your cities throughout your land which the Lord your God
        has given you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Then you will eat the offspring of your own body [to avoid starvation],
        the flesh of your sons and daughters whom the Lord your God has given you,
        during the siege and the misery by which your enemy will oppress you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The man who is most refined and well-bred among you will be cruel
        and hostile toward his brother and toward the wife he cherishes and toward
        the rest of his children who remain, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'so that he will not give even one of them any of the flesh of his
        children which he will eat, because he has nothing else left, during the
        siege and the misery by which your enemy will oppress you in all your cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'The most refined and well-bred woman among you, who would not venture
        to set the sole of her foot on the ground because she is so delicate and
        pampered, will be cruel and hostile toward the husband she cherishes and
        toward her son and daughter, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'and toward her afterbirth that comes from between her legs and toward
        the children whom she bears; for she will eat them secretly for lack of anything
        else, during the siege and the misery by which your enemy will oppress you
        in your cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "\u201CIf you are not careful to do all the words of this law that
        are written in this book, to fear and honor with reverence this glorious
        and awesome name, the Lord your God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'then the Lord will bring extraordinary plagues on you and your descendants,
        even severe and lasting plagues, and miserable and chronic sicknesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'Moreover, He will bring on you all the diseases of Egypt of which
        you were afraid, and they will cling to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Also the Lord will bring on you every sickness and every plague which
        is not written in this book of this law, until you are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Because you did not obey the voice of the Lord your God, you who
        were as numerous as the stars of heaven shall be left few in number. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'It shall come about that just as the Lord delighted over you to make
        you prosper and multiply, so the Lord will delight over you to bring you
        to ruin and destruction; and you will be uprooted [violently] from the land
        which you are entering to possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'And the Lord will scatter you among all the nations, from one end
        of the earth to the other; and there you will [be forced to] serve other
        gods, [lifeless gods of] wood and stone, which neither you nor your fathers
        have known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'Among those nations you will find no peace (rest), and there will
        be no resting place for the sole of your foot; but there the Lord will give
        you a trembling heart, failing eyes, and a despairing soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'Your life will hang in doubt before you; night and day you will be
        filled with anxiety and have no assurance of living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "In the morning you will say, \u2018I wish it were evening!\u2019
        and in the evening you will say, \u2018I wish it were morning!\u2019\u2014because
        of the dread in your heart with which you tremble, and because of the sight
        of your eyes which you will see. "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "The Lord will bring you back to Egypt in ships, by the way about
        which I said to you, \u2018You will never see it again!\u2019 And there you
        will offer yourselves for sale to your enemies as male and female slaves,
        but there will be no one to buy you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Covenant in Moab'
      title: The Covenant in Moab
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the words of the covenant which the Lord commanded Moses
        to make with the sons of Israel in the land of Moab, in addition to the covenant
        which He made with them at Horeb (Sinai).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  Moses summoned all Israel and said to them, \u201CYou have seen
        all that the Lord did before your eyes in the land of Egypt to Pharaoh, to
        all his servants, and to all his land; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the great trials [of Pharaoh] which your eyes have seen, the signs
        and those great wonders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet to this day the Lord has not given you a heart and mind to understand,
        nor eyes to see, nor ears to hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I have led you in the wilderness forty years; your clothes have not
        worn out on you, and your sandals have not worn out on your feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have not eaten bread, nor have you drunk wine or strong drink,
        so that you might know that I am the Lord your God [on whom you must depend]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When you reached this place, Sihon the king of Heshbon and Og the
        king of Bashan came out to meet us in battle, but we defeated them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and we took their land and gave it as an inheritance to the tribe
        of Reuben, the tribe of Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So keep the words of this covenant and obey them, so that you may
        prosper and be successful in everything that you do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAll of you stand today before the Lord your God\u2014your chiefs,
        your tribes, your elders and your officers, even all the men of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "your little ones, your wives, and the stranger (resident alien, foreigner)
        who is in your camps, from the one who chops and gathers your firewood to
        the one who draws your water\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so that you may enter into the covenant of the Lord your God, and
        into His oath and agreement which the Lord your God is making with you today, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'so that He may establish you today as His people and that He may
        be your God, just as He spoke to you and as He swore to your fathers, to
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIt is not with you alone that I am making this covenant and
        this oath, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but with those [future Israelites] who are not here with us today,
        as well as with those who stand here with us today in the presence of the
        Lord our God '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '(for you know how we lived in the land of Egypt, and how we passed
        through the nations along the way; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and you have seen their detestable acts and their [repulsive] idols
        of wood and stone, [lifeless images] of silver and gold, which they had with
        them), '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that there will not be among you a man or woman, or family or
        tribe, whose heart turns away today from the Lord our God, to go and serve
        the [false] gods of these nations; so that there will not be among you a
        root [of idolatry] bearing poisonous fruit and wormwood (bitterness). '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "It will happen that when he (a renegade) hears the words of this
        oath, and he imagines himself as blessed, saying, \u2018I will have peace
        and safety even though I walk within the stubbornness of my heart [rejecting
        God and His law], in order that the watered land dwindles away along with
        the dry [destroying everything],\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the Lord will not be willing to forgive him, but then the anger of
        the Lord and His jealousy will burn against that man, and every curse which
        is written in this book will rest on him; the Lord will blot out his name
        from under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the Lord will single him out for disaster from all the tribes
        of Israel [making an example of him], according to all the curses of the
        covenant that are written in this Book of the Law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the next generation, your children who come after you and the
        foreigner who comes from a distant land, when they see the plagues of this
        land and the diseases with which the Lord has afflicted it, will say, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018The whole land is brimstone and salt, a burning waste, unsown
        and unproductive, and no grass grows in it; it is like the overthrow of Sodom
        and Gomorrah, Admah and Zeboiim, which the Lord overthrew in His anger and
        wrath.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "All the nations will say, \u2018Why has the Lord done this thing
        to this land? Why this great outburst of anger?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then people will say, \u2018It is because they abandoned (broke)
        the covenant of the Lord, the God of their fathers, which He made with them
        when He brought them out of the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For they went and served other gods and worshiped them, [false] gods
        whom they have not known and whom He had not allotted (given) to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So the anger of the Lord burned against this land, bringing on it
        every curse that is written in this book; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and the Lord uprooted them from their land in anger and in wrath
        and in great indignation, and cast them into another land, as it is this
        day.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThe secret things belong to the Lord our God, but the things
        which are revealed and disclosed belong to us and to our children forever,
        so that we may do all of the words of this law."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restoration Promised'
      title: Restoration Promised
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CSo it shall be when all these things have come on you, the
        blessing and the curse which I have set before you, and you call them to
        mind in all the nations where the Lord your God has driven you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and you have returned to the Lord your God and have listened to and
        obeyed His voice with all your heart and with all your soul, in accordance
        with everything that I am commanding you today, you and your children, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'then the Lord your God will restore your fortunes [in your return
        from exile], and have compassion on you, and will gather you together again
        from all the peoples (nations) where He has scattered you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Even if any of your dispersed are at the ends of the earth, the Lord
        your God will gather you together from there, and from there He will bring
        you back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The Lord your God will bring you into the land which your fathers
        possessed, and you will take possession of it; and He shall make you prosper
        and multiply\u2014even more than your fathers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd the Lord your God will circumcise your heart and the hearts
        of your descendants [that is, He will remove the desire to sin from your
        heart], so that you will love the Lord your God with all your heart and all
        your soul, so that you may live [as a recipient of His blessing]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord your God will inflict all these curses on your enemies and
        on those who hate you, who have persecuted you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you shall again listen to and obey the voice of the Lord, and
        do all His commandments which I command you today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the Lord your God shall make you abundantly prosperous in everything
        that you do, in the offspring of your body and in the offspring of your cattle
        and in the produce of your land; for the Lord will again delight over you
        for good, just as He delighted over your fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'if you listen to and obey the voice of the Lord your God to keep
        His commandments and His statutes which are written in this Book of the Law,
        and if you turn to the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your
        soul (your entire being).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFor this commandment which I am commanding you today is not
        too difficult for you, nor is it out of reach. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It is not [a secret hidden] in heaven, that you should say, \u2018Who
        will go up to heaven for us and bring it to us, so that we may hear it and
        obey it?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Nor is it beyond the sea, that you should say, \u2018Who will cross
        the sea for us and bring it to us, so that we may hear it and obey it?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Choose Life'
      title: Choose Life
      number: 14
      content: 'But the word is very near you, in your mouth and in your heart, so
        that you may obey it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CListen closely, I have set before you today life and prosperity
        (good), and death and adversity (evil); "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'in that I command you today to love the Lord your God, to walk [that
        is, to live each and every day] in His ways and to keep His commandments
        and His statutes and His judgments (precepts), so that you will live and
        multiply, and that the Lord your God will bless you in the land which you
        are entering to possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But if your heart turns away and you will not hear and obey, but
        are drawn away and worship other gods and serve them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I declare to you today that you will certainly perish. You will not
        live long in the land which you cross the Jordan to enter and possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I call heaven and earth as witnesses against you today, that I have
        set before you life and death, the blessing and the curse; therefore, you
        shall choose life in order that you may live, you and your descendants, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "by loving the Lord your God, by obeying His voice, and by holding
        closely to Him; for He is your life [your good life, your abundant life,
        your fulfillment] and the length of your days, that you may live in the land
        which the Lord promised (swore) to give to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac,
        and Jacob.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Moses\u2019 Last Counsel"
      title: "Moses\u2019 Last Counsel"
      number: 1
      content: '  So Moses went and spoke these words to all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CI am a hundred and twenty years old today;
        I am no longer able to come in and go out [as your spiritual and military
        leader], and the Lord has said to me, \u2018You shall not cross this Jordan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It is the Lord your God who will cross ahead of you; He will destroy
        these nations before you, and you shall dispossess them. Joshua is the one
        who will go across before you [to lead you], just as the Lord has said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord will do to them just as He did to Sihon and Og, the kings
        of the Amorites, and to their land, when He destroyed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord will hand them over to you, and you shall do to them in
        accordance with all the commandments which I have commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Be strong and courageous, do not be afraid or tremble in dread before
        them, for it is the Lord your God who goes with you. He will not fail you
        or abandon you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Moses called to Joshua and said to him in the sight of all [the
        people of] Israel, \u201CBe strong and courageous, for you will go with this
        people into the land which the Lord has sworn to their fathers to give them,
        and you will give it to them as an inheritance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It is the Lord who goes before you; He will be with you. He will
        not fail you or abandon you. Do not fear or be dismayed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Moses wrote this law and gave it to the priests, the sons of Levi
        who carried the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and to all the elders of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Moses commanded them, saying, \u201CAt the end of every seven
        years, at the time of year when debts are forgiven, at the Feast of Booths
        (Tabernacles), "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'when all Israel comes to appear before the Lord your God in the place
        which He chooses, you shall read this law before all [the people of] Israel
        so that they may hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Assemble the people, the men and the women and children and the stranger
        (resident alien, foreigner) within your cities, so that they may hear and
        learn and fear the Lord your God [with awe-filled reverence and profound
        respect], and be careful to obey all the words of this law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Israel Will Fall Away'
      title: Israel Will Fall Away
      number: 13
      content: "Their children, who have not known [the law], will hear and learn
        to fear [and worship] the Lord your God, as long as you live in the land
        which you are crossing the Jordan to possess.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CBehold, the time for you to die
        is near; call Joshua, and present yourselves at the Tent of Meeting, so that
        I may commission him.\u201D So Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves
        at the Tent of Meeting. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Lord appeared in the tent in a pillar of cloud, and the
        pillar of cloud stood beside the doorway of the tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Lord said to Moses, \u201CBehold, you are about to lie down [in
        death] with your fathers; and this people will arise and play the prostitute
        (commit apostasy) with the foreign gods [of the people] of the land, where
        they go to be among them. They will abandon (turn away from) Me and break
        My covenant which I have made with them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then My anger will be kindled and burn against them in that day,
        and I will abandon (turn away from) them and hide My face from them. They
        will be devoured, and many evils and troubles will come on them, so that
        they will say in that day, \u2018Is it not because our God is not among us
        that these evils have come on us?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But I will certainly hide My face [from them] in that day because
        of all the evil which they will do, for they will turn to other gods [to
        worship lifeless idols, to honor handmade relics].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CNow then, write this song for yourselves, and teach it to the
        sons of Israel; put it in their mouth, so that this song may be a witness
        for Me against the sons of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For when I bring them into the land which I have sworn to their fathers,
        a land [of plenty] flowing with milk and honey, and they have eaten and are
        satisfied and become prosperous, then they will turn to other gods and serve
        them, and despise and reject Me and break My covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then it shall come about, when many evils and troubles have come
        on them, that this [sacred] song will confront them as a witness; for it
        will not be forgotten from the mouth of their descendants. For I know their
        inclination which is developing even now, before I bring them into the land
        which I have sworn to give them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Joshua Is Commissioned'
      title: Joshua Is Commissioned
      number: 22
      content: 'So Moses wrote this song the same day, and taught it to the children
        of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then He commanded and commissioned Joshua, the son of Nun, and said,
        \u201CBe strong and courageous, for you will bring the sons of Israel into
        the land which I have sworn to give them, and I will be with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And when Moses completely finished writing the words of this law
        in a book, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'he commanded the Levites who carried the ark of the covenant of the
        Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CTake this Book of the Law and put it beside the ark of the
        covenant of the Lord your God, so that it may remain there as a witness against
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For I know your rebellion and contention and your stubbornness; behold,
        while I am still alive with you today, you have been rebellious against the
        Lord; how much more, then, after my death? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Assemble before me all the elders of your tribes and your officers,
        so that I may speak these words in their hearing and call heaven and earth
        as witnesses against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For I know that after my death you will behave corruptly and turn
        from the way which I have commanded you; and evil will come upon you in the
        latter days, because you will do evil in the sight of the Lord, provoking
        Him to anger with the work of your hands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Moses spoke in the hearing of all the congregation of Israel
        the words of this song, until they were ended:'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Moses'
      title: The Song of Moses
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CListen, O heavens, and I will speak;And let the earth hear
        the words of my mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let my teaching drop as the rain,My speech distill as the dew,As
        the light rain upon the tender grass,And as the spring showers upon the herb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I proclaim the name [and presence] of the Lord;Ascribe greatness
        and honor to our God!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Rock! His work is perfect,For all His ways are just;A God of
        faithfulness without iniquity (injustice),Just and upright is He.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They (Israel) have acted corruptly toward Him.They are not His children,
        because of their [moral] defect;  But are a perverse and crooked generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do you thus repay the Lord,O foolish and unwise people?Is not He
        your Father who has acquired you [as His own]?He has made you and established
        you [as a nation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember the days of old,Consider the years of many generations.Ask
        your father, and he will inform you,Your elders, and they will tell you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Most High gave the nations their inheritance,When He separated
        the sons of man,He set the boundaries of the peoplesAccording to the number
        of the sons of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the Lord\u2019s portion and chosen share is His people;Jacob
        (Israel) is the allotment of His inheritance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He found him in a desert land,In the howling wasteland of a wilderness;He
        kept circling him, He took care of him,He protected him as the apple of His
        eye.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As an eagle that protects its nest,That flutters over its young,He
        spread out His wings and took them,He carried them on His pinions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the Lord alone led him;There was no foreign god with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He made him (Israel) ride on the high places of the earth,And he
        ate the produce of the field;And He made him suck honey from the rock,And
        [olive] oil from the flinty rock,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Butter and curds of cows, and milk of the flock,With fat of lambs,And
        rams, the breed of Bashan, and goats,With the finest of the wheat;And you
        drank wine, the blood of grapes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut Jeshurun (Israel) became fat and kicked [at God].You became
        fat, thick, sleek, and obstinate!Then he abandoned God who had made him,And
        scorned the Rock of his salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They provoked Him to jealousy with strange gods [by denying Him the
        honor and loyalty that is rightfully and uniquely His];And with repulsive
        acts they provoked Him to anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They sacrificed to demons, not to God,To gods whom they have not
        known,New gods who came lately,Whom your fathers never feared.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You were unmindful of the Rock who bore you,And you forgot the God
        who gave you birth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe Lord saw it, and rejected them,Out of indignation with
        His sons and His daughters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then He said, \u2018I will hide My face from them,I will see what
        their end shall be;For they are a perverse generation,Sons in whom there
        is no faithfulness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They have made Me jealous with what is not God;They have provoked
        Me to anger with their idols.So I will make them jealous with those who are
        not a people;I will provoke them to anger with a foolish nation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For a fire is kindled by My anger,And it burns to the depths of Sheol
        (the place of the dead, the nether world),It devours the earth with its yield,And
        sets on fire the foundations of the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018I will heap misfortunes on them;I will use My arrows on them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They will be wasted by hunger, and consumed by plagueAnd a bitter
        destruction;And I will send the teeth of beasts against them,With the venom
        of crawling things of the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Outside the sword will bereave,And inside [the chambers] terror\u2014For
        both young man and virgin,For the nursing child and the man of gray hair.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I would have said, \u201CI will cut them to pieces [scattering them
        far away],I will remove the memory of them from men,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Had I not feared the provocation of the enemy,That their adversaries
        would misjudge,That they would say, \u201COur [own] hand has prevailed,And
        the Lord has not done all this.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CFor they are a nation devoid of counsel,And there is no understanding
        in them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'O that they were wise, that they understood this,That they could
        discern their future and ultimate fate!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'How could one chase a thousand,And two put ten thousand to flight,Unless
        their Rock had sold them,And the Lord had given them up?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For their rock is not like our Rock,Even our enemies themselves judge
        this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For their vine is from the vine of Sodom,And from the fields of Gomorrah;Their
        grapes are grapes of poison,Their clusters, bitter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Their wine is the venom of serpents,And the deadly poison of vipers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u2018Is it not laid up in store with Me,Sealed up in My treasuries?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Vengeance is Mine, and retribution,In due time their foot will slip;For
        the day of their disaster is at hand,And their doom hurries to meet them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For the Lord will vindicate His people,And will have compassion on
        His servants,When He sees that their strength (hand) is gone,And none remains,
        whether bond or free.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And He will say, \u2018Where are their gods,The rock in which they
        took refuge?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Who ate the fat of their sacrifices,And drank the wine of their drink
        offering?Let them rise up and help you,Let them be your hiding place!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'See now that I, I am He,And there is no god besides Me;It is I who
        put to death and I who give life.I have wounded and it is I who heal,And
        there is no one who can deliver from [the power of] My hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Indeed, I lift up My hand to heaven,And say (swear an oath), as I
        live forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'If I sharpen the lightning of My sword,And My hand takes hold of
        judgment,I will render vengeance on My adversaries,And I will repay those
        who hate Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "I will make My arrows drunk with blood,And My sword will devour flesh,With
        the blood of the slain and the captives,From the heads of the leaders of
        the enemy.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Rejoice, O nations, with His people;For He will avenge the blood
        of His servants,And will render vengeance on His adversaries,And will atone
        for His land and His people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Then Moses came and spoke all the words of this song in the hearing
        of the people, he and Joshua the son of Nun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'When Moses had finished speaking all these words to all [the people
        of] Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "he said to them, \u201CTake to heart all the words of warning which
        I am speaking to you today; and you shall command your children to observe
        them carefully\u2014to do all the words of this law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "For it is not an empty or trivial matter for you; indeed it is your
        [very] life. By [honoring and obeying] this word you will live long in the
        land, which you are crossing the Jordan to possess.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And the Lord said to Moses that very same day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u201CGo up to this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is
        in the land of Moab opposite Jericho, and look at the land of Canaan, which
        I am giving to the sons of Israel as a possession. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then die on the mountain which you climb, and be gathered to your
        people [in death], just as Aaron your brother died on Mount Hor and was gathered
        to his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'because you broke faith with Me among of the sons of Israel at the
        waters of Meribah-kadesh, in the Wilderness of Zin, and because you did not
        treat Me as holy among of the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "For you shall see the land opposite you from a distance, but you
        shall not go there, into the land which I am giving to the children of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Blessing of Moses'
      title: The Blessing of Moses
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the blessing with which Moses the man of God blessed the
        sons of Israel before his death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said,\u201CThe Lord came from Sinai,And dawned on them from Seir;He
        shone forth from Mount Paran,And He came from among ten thousand holy ones;At
        His right hand was a flaming fire, a law, for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Indeed, He loves His people;All Your holy ones are in Your hand.They
        followed in Your steps;They accept and receive direction from You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moses commanded us with a law,As a possession for the assembly of
        Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord was King in Jeshurun (Israel),When the heads of the people
        were gathered,The tribes of Israel together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMay [the tribe of] Reuben live and not die out,  But let his
        men be few.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And [Moses said] this of Judah:\u201CHear, O Lord, the voice of Judah,And
        bring him to his people.With his hands he contended for them,And may You
        be a help against his enemies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Of Levi he said,\u201CYour Thummim and Your Urim belong to Your godly
        man [Aaron],Whom You tested and proved at Massah,With whom You contended
        at the waters of Meribah;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Who said of his father and mother,\u2018I did not consider them\u2019;Nor
        did he acknowledge his brothers,Nor did he regard his own sons,For the priests
        observed Your word,And kept Your covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The priests shall teach Your ordinances (judgments) to Jacob,And
        Your law to Israel.They shall put incense before You,And whole burnt offerings
        on Your altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "O Lord, bless Levi\u2019s substance (ability),And accept and take
        pleasure in the work of his hands;Crush and shatter the loins of those who
        rise up against him,And of those who hate him, so that they do not rise again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Of Benjamin he said,\u201CMay the beloved of the Lord  dwell in safety
        by Him;He shields and covers him all the day long,And he dwells between His
        shoulders.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And of Joseph he said,\u201CBlessed by the Lord be his land,With
        the precious things of heaven, with the dew,And from the deep water that
        lies beneath,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'With the precious fruits of the sun,And with the precious produce
        of the months.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'With the best things of the ancient mountains,And with the precious
        things of the everlasting hills,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'With the precious things of the earth and its fullness,And the favor
        and goodwill of Him who dwelt in the bush.Let these blessings come upon the
        head of Joseph,And upon the crown of the head of him who was distinguished
        [as a prince] among his brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "His majesty is like a firstborn young bull,And his horns like the
        horns of the wild ox;With them he will gore the peoples,All of them together,
        to the ends of the earth.And those are the ten thousands of Ephraim,And those
        are the thousands of Manasseh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Of Zebulun he said,\u201CRejoice, Zebulun, in your interests abroad,And,
        Issachar, in your tents [at home].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They will call the peoples to the mountain (Mount Carmel);There they
        will offer sacrifices of righteousness;For they will draw out the abundance
        of the seas,And the hidden treasures of the sand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Of Gad he said,\u201CBlessed is the one who enlarges Gad;He lurks
        like a lioness,And tears the arm and the crown of the head.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He selected the best [land] for himself,For there the leader\u2019s
        portion was reserved;Yet he came with the leaders of the people;He carried
        out the justice (righteous will) of the Lord,And His ordinances (judgments)
        with Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Of Dan he said,\u201CDan is a lion\u2019s cub,That leaps forth from
        Bashan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Of Naphtali he said,\u201CO Naphtali, satisfied with favor,And full
        of the blessing of the Lord,Take possession of the sea [of Galilee] and the
        south.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Of Asher he said,\u201CMore blessed than sons is Asher;May he be
        favored by his brothers,And may he dip his foot in oil.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your strongholds will be iron and bronze,And as your days are, so
        will your strength, your rest and security be.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThere is none like the God of Jeshurun (Israel),Who rides the
        heavens to your help,And through the skies in His majestic glory.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The eternal God is your refuge and dwelling place,And underneath
        are the everlasting arms;He drove out the enemy from before you,And said,
        \u2018Destroy!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Israel dwells in safety and security,The fountain of Jacob alone
        and secluded,In a land of grain and new wine;His heavens also drop down dew.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Happy and blessed are you, O Israel;Who is like you, a people saved
        by the Lord,The Shield of your help,And the Sword of your majesty!Your enemies
        will cringe before you,And you will tread on their high places [tramping
        down their idolatrous altars].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Moses'
      title: The Death of Moses
      number: 1
      content: '    Now Moses went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the
        top of Pisgah, that is opposite Jericho. And the Lord showed him all the
        land, from Gilead to Dan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and all Naphtali and the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, and all the
        land of Judah to the western sea (Mediterranean Sea), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the Negev (South country) and the plain in the Valley of Jericho,
        the city of palm trees, as far as Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u201CThis is the land which I swore to
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, \u2018I will give it to your descendants.\u2019
        I have let you see it with your eyes, but you shall not go over there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Moses the servant of the Lord died there in the land of Moab,
        according to the word of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And He buried him in the valley in the land of Moab, opposite Beth-peor;
        but no man knows where his burial place is to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Although Moses was a hundred and twenty years old when he died, his
        eyesight was not dim, nor his natural strength abated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the sons of Israel wept for Moses in the plains of Moab for thirty
        days; then the days of weeping and mourning for Moses were ended.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now Joshua the son of Nun was filled with the spirit of wisdom, for
        Moses had laid his hands on him; so the sons of Israel listened to him and
        did as the Lord commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Since that time no prophet has risen in Israel like Moses, whom the
        Lord knew face to face, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '[none equal to him] in all the signs and wonders which the Lord sent
        him to perform in the land of Egypt against Pharaoh, all his servants, and
        all his land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: and in all the mighty power and all the great and terrible deeds which
        Moses performed in the sight of all Israel.
      comments: []
